prtBertSyncLoss.description: How many times Sync Loss was detected since BERT started to run. For some products: number of seconds in which Sync Loss occured since BERT started to run. See product specification.

prtBertErrorBits.name: prtBertErrorBits
prtBertErrorBits.description: How many Error Bits were detected since BERT started to run.

prtBertClearCounters.name: prtBertClearCounters
prtBertClearCounters.description: Setting this object to ON, will enforce a clear operation of some BERT Counters. Upon completion, the value will automatically change to off(2).

prtBertTs.name: prtBertTs
prtBertTs.description: This object indicates on which TSs of the selected port, BERT should be applied. Each Bit of the Octet represents a TS: 31 ......0 MSB LSB Bit 0 will not be used. If the bit value is '1' - BERT should be applied on this TS. For a T1 port, the valid raised bits ('1') are: 1..25. For an E1 port, the valid raised bits ('1') are: 1..31. Agents that do not support this feature will send SIZE 0.

prtBertResult.name: prtBertResult
prtBertResult.description: This object indicates Result of BERT for the selected port (number of error bits divided to the total number of data bits.) Applicable only if BERT is running on this port Agents that do not support this feature will send SIZE 0.

prtBertTxBits.name: prtBertTxBits
prtBertTxBits.description: How many data bits were transmitted since BERT started to run, or since last counter clear (prtBertClearCounters set to on).

prtBertRxBits.name: prtBertRxBits
prtBertRxBits.description: How many data bits were Received since BERT started to run, or since last counter clear (prtBertClearCounters set to on).

prtBertTxErrorBits.name: prtBertTxErrorBits
prtBertTxErrorBits.description: Number of injected error bits since BERT started to run, or since last counter clear (prtBertClearCounters set to on).

prtMonTable.name: prtMonTable
prtMonTable.description: For DXC, the write operation into the Table's Objects is valid only for the TmpCnfg entry (Scratch).

prtMonCnfgIdx.name: prtMonCnfgIdx
prtMonCnfgIdx.description: This object indicates the Idx of the Cnfg(1..255) being accessed. Idx of 255 relates to the TmpCnfg. For products that do not support configurations, 1 will be always used.

prtMonitoringIdx.name: prtMonitoringIdx
prtMonitoringIdx.description: This object indicates the Monitoring Port Index. For DXC: The valid port number depends on the IO slot no., the installed card type and the port type: external, internal. * The external ports will according to the convention (for DXC): - first two digits will be: (IO slot number+10) - last one/two digits will be the port number within the card, in odd numbers: port1 = 1 port2 = 3 port3 = 5 etc... Example: port2 of IO slot 11 will be: 213 . * The internal ports will be according to the convention (for DXC): - first two digits will be: (IO slot number+10) - last one/two digits will be the port number within the card, in even numbers: port1 = 2 port2 = 4 port3 = 6 etc... Example: port2 of IO slot 11 will be: 214 . For Optimux-T3: 255 (Not Applicable) will be always used. The Monitoring port is always the Station Clock (not considered an interface).

prtMonitoringEnable.name: prtMonitoringEnable
prtMonitoringEnable.description: This object indicates if the prtMonitoringIdx is configured as a monitoring port or not. disabled = the port is NOT configured to monitor. Setting this object to this value will cause reset (to 0) of the prtMonitoringTSs and prtMonitoredTSs objects. enabled = the port IS configured to monitor. For Optimux-T3: always enabled (RO supported).

prtMonitoringTSs.name: prtMonitoringTSs
prtMonitoringTSs.description: This object indicates which TSs of the Monitoring port, the test equipment should monitor. Each Bit of the Octet represents a TS: 31 ......0 MSB LSB Bit 0 will not be used. If the bit value is '1' - this TS should be monitored. For a T1 port, the valid raised bits ('1') are: 1..24. For an E1 port, the valid raised bits ('1') are: 1..31. Default: all bits='0' Agents that do not support this feature will send SIZE 0. This object can be Set as described only if prtMonitoringEnable=enabled.

prtMonitoredPort.name: prtMonitoredPort
prtMonitoredPort.description: This object indicates the MONITORED Port Index that the Monitoring port monitors. For DXC: The valid port number depends on the IO slot no., the installed card type and the port type: external, internal. * The external ports will according to the convention (for DXC): - first two digits will be: (IO slot number+10) - last one/two digits will be the port number within the card, in odd numbers: port1 = 1 port2 = 3 port3 = 5 etc... Example: port2 of IO slot 11 will be: 213 . * The internal ports will be according to the convention (for DXC): - first two digits will be: (IO slot number+10) - last one/two digits will be the port number within the card, in even numbers: port1 = 2 port2 = 4 port3 = 6 etc... Example: port2 of IO slot 11 will be: 214 . * 100 - no port monitored For Optimux-T3: The valid channels are: 0 = no Ch monitored 1..21 or 1..28 (=CH1..CH21 or CH1..CH28) according to product's configuration.

prtMonitoredTSs.name: prtMonitoredTSs
prtMonitoredTSs.description: This object indicates which TSs of the Monitored port, should be monitored. Each Bit of the Octet represents a TS: 31 ......0 MSB LSB Bit 0 will not be used. If the bit value is '1' - this TS should be monitored. For a T1 port, the valid raised bits ('1') are: 1..24. For an E1 port, the valid raised bits ('1') are: 1..31. Default: all bits='0' Agents that do not support this feature will send SIZE 0. This object can be Set as described only if prtMonitoringEnable=enabled.

prtCfgParamTable.name: prtCfgParamTable
prtCfgParamTable.description: The write operation into the Table Objects is valid only to the TmpCnfg entry. KMUX parameters are for the cards: KMBE/New, KVF.6 family.

prtCfgParamCnfgIdx.name: prtCfgParamCnfgIdx
prtCfgParamCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

prtCfgParamIdx.name: prtCfgParamIdx
prtCfgParamIdx.description: A unique identifier of the port (within the card when applicable). - For KM-2100: Slot*100+Ch external ports: Ch=1..10 internal ports (sub-channels): Ch=11..20. - For FCD-T1/E1(L): MAIN=111, SUB=113, CH1=122, CH2=124.

prtCfgParamSlt.name: prtCfgParamSlt
prtCfgParamSlt.description: This attribute indicates a unique number to identify the slot where the card is inserted in. In the 2104 Unit the entries kmxIO5(111)..kmxIO12(118) are not valid. notApplicable(255) - for products that do not have Slots.

prtCfgParamOperatedMl.name: prtCfgParamOperatedMl
prtCfgParamOperatedMl.description: The main link for this channel. The field is relevant only for ML modes of Dual, Priority Bumping and Switched Backup.

prtCfgParamMlAtoMlBPrio.name: prtCfgParamMlAtoMlBPrio
prtCfgParamMlAtoMlBPrio.description: ML-A to ML-B Priority. The field is relevant only for ML modes of Priority Bumping and Switched Backup.

prtCfgParamMlBtoMlAPrio.name: prtCfgParamMlBtoMlAPrio
prtCfgParamMlBtoMlAPrio.description: ML-B to ML-A Priority. The field is relevant only for ML modes of Priority Bumping.

prtCfgParamInbandLoopDetection.name: prtCfgParamInbandLoopDetection
prtCfgParamInbandLoopDetection.description: Inband Loop Detection. The field is relevant for FCD-T1/E1(L) ports.

prtCfgParamInbandLoopPatternCfg.name: prtCfgParamInbandLoopPatternCfg
prtCfgParamInbandLoopPatternCfg.description: This object indicates if Inband Loop polynomial pattern will be according to RDL Loop (the standard) or User Configurated according to prtCfgParamInbandLoopActPattern and prtCfgParamInbandLoopDeactPattern.

prtCfgParamInbandLoopActPattern.name: prtCfgParamInbandLoopActPattern
prtCfgParamInbandLoopActPattern.description: This object is a binary string of up to 8 bits. Though the syntax allows for any ASCII characters, for this object only '0' or '1' characters are valid. The string determines coefficients of the polynomial pattern sent to the port in order to Activate the Inband Loop. This object is relevant only when prtCfgParamInbandLoopPatternCfg=userConfig.

prtCfgParamInbandLoopDeactPattern.name: prtCfgParamInbandLoopDeactPattern
prtCfgParamInbandLoopDeactPattern.description: This object is a binary string of up to 8 bits. Though the syntax allows for any ASCII characters, for this object only '0' or '1' characters are valid. The string determines coefficients of the polynomial pattern sent to the port in order to Deactivate the Inband Loop. This object is relevant only when prtCfgParamInbandLoopPatternCfg=userConfig.

prtT1E1StatEntry.name: prtT1E1StatEntry
prtT1E1StatEntry.description: An entry in the T1/E1 port statistics table.

prtT1E1SPrtIdx.name: prtT1E1SPrtIdx
prtT1E1SPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number. The same numbering as for prtGenPrtIdx. The valid port number depends on the IO slot no., the installed card type and the port type: outside, inside. * The outside ports will be the T1/E1 cards ports. The convention used will be (for DXC): - first two digits will be: (IO slot number+10) - last one/two digits will be the port number within the card, in odd numbers: port1 = 1 port2 = 3 port3 = 5 etc... Example: port2 of IO slot 11 will be: 213 .

prtT1E1SSlt.name: prtT1E1SSlt
prtT1E1SSlt.description: This attribute indicates a unique number to identify the slot where the card is inserted in. When the unit is stand-alone, this object is not applicable and 255 will be used.

prtT1E1OosCount.name: prtT1E1OosCount
prtT1E1OosCount.description: This object is applicable only for an E1 active port. It provides the number of red alarm events since the last count clearing.

prtT1E1BpvLastMin.name: prtT1E1BpvLastMin
prtT1E1BpvLastMin.description: This object is applicable only for an E1 active port. It provides the number of BPV (BiPolar Violation) events detected during the last minute.

prtT1E1BpvMax.name: prtT1E1BpvMax
prtT1E1BpvMax.description: This object is applicable only for an E1 active port. It provides the maximal number of BPV (BiPolar Violation) events (per minute), detected during the worst minute.

prtT1E1CnfgEntry.name: prtT1E1CnfgEntry
prtT1E1CnfgEntry.description: An entry in the T1/E1 port configuration table.

prtT1E1CnfgIdx.name: prtT1E1CnfgIdx
prtT1E1CnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Config being accessed. Idx of 255 relates to the Temporary (Scratch) Config.

prtT1E1PrtIdx.name: prtT1E1PrtIdx
prtT1E1PrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number. The same numbering as for prtGenPrtIdx. The valid port number depends on the IO slot no., the installed card type and the port type: outside, inside. In the DXC : - first two digits will be: (IO slot number+10) - last one/two digits will be the port number within the card in odd or even numbers, as follows: * For the outside/external ports, in odd numbers: port1 = 1 port2 = 3 port3 = 5 etc... Example: port2 of IO slot 11 will be: 213 . * The inside/internal ports, in even numbers: port1 = 2 port2 = 4 port3 = 6 etc... Example: port2 of IO slot 11 will be: 214 . In the Kilomux, the port index is calculated as follows: 100*Slot+Ch. The external Ch numbers are 1..10, and the internal Ch numbers are 11..20.

prtT1E1Slt.name: prtT1E1Slt
prtT1E1Slt.description: This attribute indicates a unique number to identify the slot where the card is inserted in. When the unit is stand-alone, this object is not applicable and 255 will be used.

prtT1E1LineType.name: prtT1E1LineType
prtT1E1LineType.description: This variable indicates the variety of T1/E1 Line implementing this circuit. The type of circuit affects the number of bits per second that the circuit can reasonably carry, as well as the interpretation of the usage and error statistics. The values, in sequence, describe: TITLE: SPECIFICATION: esf Extended SuperFrame DS1 d4 AT&T D4 format DS1 - SF e1 CCITT Recommendation G.704 (Table 4a) - G732N e1Crc CCITT Recommendation G.704 (Table 4b) - G732N with CRC e1MF G.704 (Table 4a) with TS16 multiframing enabled - G732S e1CrcMF G.704 (Table 4b) with TS16 multiframing enabled - G732S with CRC unframed T1 - applicable values: (1),(2),(3),(8) E1 - applicable values: (1),(4),(5),(6),(7),(8)

prtT1E1LineCode.name: prtT1E1LineCode
prtT1E1LineCode.description: This variable describes the variety of Zero Code Suppression used on the link, which in turn affects a number of its characteristics. jbzs=b7zs refers the Jammed Bit Zero Suppres- sion, in which the AT&T specification of at least one pulse every 8 bit periods is literal- ly implemented by forcing a pulse in bit 8 of each channel. Thus, only seven bits per chan- nel, or 1.344 Mbps, is available for data (used for T1). b8zs refers to the use of a specified pattern of normal bits and bipolar violations which are used to replace a sequence of eight zero bits (used for T1). ANSI Clear Channels may use zbtsi, or Zero Byte Time Slot Interchange. E1 links, with or without CRC, use hdb3 or ami (= TRAN). amI (=TRAN) refers to a mode wherein no zero code suppression is present and the line encoding does not solve the problem directly. In this application, the higher layer must provide data which meets or exceeds the pulse density re- quirements, such as inverting HDLC data.

prtT1E1SignalMode.name: prtT1E1SignalMode
prtT1E1SignalMode.description: 'none' indicates that no bits are reserved for signaling on this channel. 'robbedBit' indicates that T1 Robbed Bit Signaling is in use. 'bitOriented' indicates that E1 Channel Associated Signaling (CAS) is in use. 'messageOriented' indicates that Common Channel Signaling (CCS) is in use either on channel 16 of an E1 link or channel 24 of a T1.

prtT1E1Fdl.name: prtT1E1Fdl
prtT1E1Fdl.description: This bitmap describes the use of the facili- ties data link, and is the sum of the capabili- ties: 'other' indicates that a protocol other than one following is used. 'ansi-T1-403' refers to the FDL exchange recommended by ANSI. 'att-54016' refers to ESF FDL exchanges. 'fdl-none' indicates that the device does not use the FDL. 'transFdl' indicates transition between two ports of the same card.

prtT1E1FdlMode.name: prtT1E1FdlMode
prtT1E1FdlMode.description: Fdl Mode of the T1 selected port. notApplicable - will be used for an E1 port.

prtT1E1Sync.name: prtT1E1Sync
prtT1E1Sync.description: This object enables returning to normal operation, after the end of a main/sub link red alarm event, in reduced time. 'tr62411' - complies with AT&T TR-62411 (after 10 seconds). Applicable for both T1 and E1 interfaces. 'ccitt' - complies with CCITT standard. Applicable only for E1 interfaces. 'fast' - after 1 second.

prtT1E1CGA.name: prtT1E1CGA
prtT1E1CGA.description: This object selects the method used to signal the CGA state to the other end, through the main/sub link. 'none' - non-transparent mode. When one of the links (main/sub) will be in Out Of Service state, both 'Data/Voice Oos' and 'Oos Signal' will be transmitted to the other end. 'trans' - when one of the links (main/sub) will be in Out Of Service state, 'Data/Voice Oos' will be transmitted to the other end. 'full' - fully-transparent mode. When one of the links (main/sub) will be in Out Of Service state, neither 'Data/Voice Oos' nor 'Oos Signal' will be transmitted to the other end.

prtT1E1IdleCode.name: prtT1E1IdleCode
prtT1E1IdleCode.description: This object selects the code transmitted to fill idle (unused) time slots in the main link frame. Valid range: (0 - FF HEX) .

prtT1E1OosSignal.name: prtT1E1OosSignal
prtT1E1OosSignal.description: 'idle' = '0' = on-hook, idle state 'busy' = '1' = off-hook, busy state 'forcedIdle' = SP = both A and B signaling bits are forced to '0' during out-of-service periods. 'forcedBusy' = MK = both A and B signaling bits are forced to '1' during out-of-service periods. 'busyIdle' = MK_SP = A and B bits are forced to '1' for 2.5 seconds; then they are switched to '0' until out-of-service condition disappears. 'idleBusy' = SP_MK = A and B bits are forced to '0' for 2.5 seconds; then they are switched to '1' until out-of-service condition disappears. - for T1: '0'=0 ; '1'=1 - for E1: '0'=1 ; '1'=0

prtT1E1VoiceOos.name: prtT1E1VoiceOos
prtT1E1VoiceOos.description: Voice Out-Of-Service code. Valid range: (0 - FF HEX). For agents that do not support this feature, the value will always be 0.

prtT1E1DataOos.name: prtT1E1DataOos
prtT1E1DataOos.description: Data Out-Of-Service code. Valid range: (0 - FF HEX). For agents that do not support this feature, the value will always be 0.

prtT1E1LineLengthMask.name: prtT1E1LineLengthMask
prtT1E1LineLengthMask.description: This attribute is the line length mask parameter used only for T1/DSU interfaces. len400p533ft=length range: 400ft to 533ft 'fcc68' - provides compliance with the FCC 68.308 Option A output pulse mask.

prtT1E1TxGainMask.name: prtT1E1TxGainMask
prtT1E1TxGainMask.description: This attribute is the tx gain mask parameter (dB), used only for T1/CSU interfaces.

prtT1E1InbandMng.name: prtT1E1InbandMng
prtT1E1InbandMng.description: A unique number to identify an Inband management over the link. internal - supported by KM-2100 only. It means that the management is internal to the frame. It takes part of the ML Frame bits (instead of data).

prtT1E1InbandMngRate.name: prtT1E1InbandMngRate
prtT1E1InbandMngRate.description: A unique number to identify the rate of the Inband management. It is required only for E1 links and is applicable only when prtExT1E1InbandMng selected is FdlOrTs0 or dedicatedTs.

prtT1E1DedicatedTs.name: prtT1E1DedicatedTs
prtT1E1DedicatedTs.description: The value is differently determined for different products. There are two methods: 1) A unique number to identify Dedicated TS of the T1/E1 port. It is applicable only when prtExT1E1InbandMng selected is dedicatedTs. 1..24 - Dedicated TS of T1 1..31 - Dedicated TS of E1 255 - notApplicable (for agents that do not support this feature) Other values are invalid. 2) For FCD-STM, up to five TSs may be dedicated to management. This object value is the Sum (sigma) of 2**n, where n =TS-1 e.g. Time slots 3,5,7,9,11 are dedicated to management: 2** 2 +2** 4 +2** 6 +2** 8 +2**10 = 4+16+64+256+1024=1364 User should consult the product specification, to find out the method employed.

prtT1E1InbandMngRoutProt.name: prtT1E1InbandMngRoutProt
prtT1E1InbandMngRoutProt.description: Inband Mng Routing Protocol of the port. When prtT1E1InbandMng is 'dedicatedPpp'-'proprietary' and 'rip2' are applicable. For other values - only 'proprietary' is applicable. For FCD-M and FCD-A: When prtT1E1InbandMng is 'dedicatedPpp' or 'dedicatedFr': 'None', 'proprietary' and 'rip2' are applicable. When prtT1E1InbandMng is 'fdlOrTS0' or 'dedicatedTs': 'None' and 'proprietary' are applicable. When prtT1E1InbandMng is 'off': 'None' is applicable.

prtT1E1LinkMode.name: prtT1E1LinkMode
prtT1E1LinkMode.description: regular - TSs are connected by user via TS Assignment only transparent - when a port with this Link Mode is connected to an internal T1/E1 port of a T3/E3 card, TS0, TS16 and Fbit are transparently transferred to the E3/T3 stream.

prtT1E1Multiplier.name: prtT1E1Multiplier
prtT1E1Multiplier.description: The data rate of each TS. The multiplier values can be 56 kbps or 64 kbps. For T1 only.

prtT1E1RxGain.name: prtT1E1RxGain
prtT1E1RxGain.description: This attribute is the rx volume (dB).

prtT1E1LineMode.name: prtT1E1LineMode
prtT1E1LineMode.description: Interface type of the port. For T1 - csu, dsu are the valid values For E1 - dsu, ltu are the valid values

prtT1E1TS0SaBits.name: prtT1E1TS0SaBits
prtT1E1TS0SaBits.description: This object is applicable only for E1 ports. For T1, string size will be 0. For E1, it enables user to select the use of TS0 Sa Bits 4..8, by 3 octets: The order (in hexa display): free Sa-Bit-4 Sa-Bit-5 Sa-Bit-6 Sa-Bit-7 Sa-Bit-8 |___________| |________________| |________________| MSByte LSByte Each Sa Bit will be represented by a nibble, having the following meaning: 0000 = zero 0001 = one 0010 = management 0011 = transparent the rest are reserved for future use.

prtT1E1ConnectedTS.name: prtT1E1ConnectedTS
prtT1E1ConnectedTS.description: This parameter indicates if there is any connected TS for this interface.

prtT1E1Ts0SaBit.name: prtT1E1Ts0SaBit
prtT1E1Ts0SaBit.description: This parameter indicates whether to send TS 0, or not. noMng= TS 0 is looped, therefore not sent. mng= TS 0 isn't looped, therefore it is sent.

prtT1E1SameFeCnfg.name: prtT1E1SameFeCnfg
prtT1E1SameFeCnfg.description: This parameter indicates whether the same E1 configuration parameters and TS assignment are set both to the local and remote device. Read-Write access is applicable only in G732N framed mode. For G732S and UNFRAMED this parameter is set by agent to YES and is Read Only. In Case of conflict during power-up between the central and remote, the value set by the central unit is the valid one.

prtT1E1RemCrc4.name: prtT1E1RemCrc4
prtT1E1RemCrc4.description: This object indicates whether the E1 of the Remote device connected to this E1 port, will have CRC-4 or not.

prtT1E1MaxTSs.name: prtT1E1MaxTSs
prtT1E1MaxTSs.description: This object is applicable only for DXC D4T1, D4E1, D8T1, D8E1 external ports and D8GSL internal E1 ports. It is relevant only when sysCIntTsAllocMode=static(2). 255=not applicable If prtT1E1LineType=unframed(8), the value of this object must be 32. Else, the valid values are 0..31.

prtT1E1EocTsConfig.name: prtT1E1EocTsConfig
prtT1E1EocTsConfig.description: This object indicates whether the use of EOC for TS Configuration is enabled or not.

prtT1E1Role.name: prtT1E1Role
prtT1E1Role.description: This object indicates whether this port behaves as SUB or Main link.

prtT1E1FdlMsgTable.name: prtT1E1FdlMsgTable
prtT1E1FdlMsgTable.description: This table is applicable for a T1 interface with 'esf' LineType or E1 interface, when CRC is enabled (LineType).

prtT1E1FdlMsgPrtIdx.name: prtT1E1FdlMsgPrtIdx
prtT1E1FdlMsgPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number. The same numbering as for prtGenPrtIdx. The valid port number depends on the IO slot no., the installed card type and the port type: outside, inside. * The outside ports will be the T1/E1 cards ports. The convention used will be (for DXC): - first two digits will be: (IO slot number+10) - last one/two digits will be the port number within the card, in odd numbers: port1 = 1 port2 = 3 port3 = 5 etc... Example: port2 of IO slot 11 will be: 213 .

prtT1E1FdlMsgFdlType.name: prtT1E1FdlMsgFdlType
prtT1E1FdlMsgFdlType.description: The Fdl type reference of the Fdl message.

prtT1E1FdlMsgSlt.name: prtT1E1FdlMsgSlt
prtT1E1FdlMsgSlt.description: This attribute indicates a unique number to identify the slot where the card is inserted in. When the unit is stand-alone, this object is not applicable and 255 will be used.

prtHSCnfgIdx.name: prtHSCnfgIdx
prtHSCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Config being accessed. Idx of 255 relates to the Temporary (Scratch) Config.

prtHSPrtIdx.name: prtHSPrtIdx
prtHSPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique number to identify a port. The valid port number depends on the IO slot no., the installed card type and the port type: outside, inside, SP. * The inside ports will be the HS cards ports. The convention used will be (for DXC): - first two digits will be: (IO slot number+10) - last one/two digits will be the port number within the card, in even numbers: port1 = 2 port2 = 4 port3 = 6 etc... Example: port2 of IO slot 11 will be: 214 .

prtHSSlt.name: prtHSSlt
prtHSSlt.description: This attribute indicates a unique number to identify the slot where the card is inserted in. When the unit is stand-alone, this object is not applicable and 255 will be used.

prtHSRate.name: prtHSRate
prtHSRate.description: This object indicates the port rate (speed). auto - rate is selected automatically by system.

prtHSFifoSize.name: prtHSFifoSize
prtHSFifoSize.description: This object selects the size of the user data channel buffer FIFO used in the DTE2 mode. In the other modes, buffer size is automatically set by the DACS agent. Buffer FIFO size in bits, corresponds to FIFO lengths of +/-16, +/-30, +/-52, +/-72 bits.

prtHSClkMode.name: prtHSClkMode
prtHSClkMode.description: Clock Mode of the user data channel. dce - DACS operates as a DCE and provides transmit and receive clocks to the synchronous user DTE. dte1- DACS supplies the receive clock to the user equipment and accepts the user transmit clock. dte2- DACS requires transmit and receive clocks from the user equipment.

prtHSCTS.name: prtHSCTS
prtHSCTS.description: Selection of CTS line state in the user data channel. on - CTS continuously ON. rts - CTS line follows the RTS line.

prtHSInbandLoopback.name: prtHSInbandLoopback
prtHSInbandLoopback.description: This object indicates if Inband Loopback from the Network should be enabled or disabled.

prtHSInbandLoopPatternCfg.name: prtHSInbandLoopPatternCfg
prtHSInbandLoopPatternCfg.description: This object indicates if Inband Loop polynomial pattern will be according to RDL Loop (the standard) or User Configurated according to prtHSActivatePolyPattern and prtHSDeactivatePolyPattern.

prtHSInbandLoopActPattern.name: prtHSInbandLoopActPattern
prtHSInbandLoopActPattern.description: This object is a binary string of up to 8 bits. Though the syntax allows for any ASCII characters, for this object only '0' or '1' characters are valid. The string determines coefficients of the polynomial pattern sent to the port in order to Activate the Inband Loop. This object is relevant only when prtHSInbandLoopPatternCfg=userConfig.

prtHSInbandLoopDeactPattern.name: prtHSInbandLoopDeactPattern
prtHSInbandLoopDeactPattern.description: This object is a binary string of up to 8 bits. Though the syntax allows for any ASCII characters, for this object only '0' or '1' characters are valid. The string determines coefficients of the polynomial pattern sent to the port in order to Deactivate the Inband Loop. This object is relevant only when prtHSInbandLoopPatternCfg=userConfig.

prtHSDCD.name: prtHSDCD
prtHSDCD.description: Selection of DCD line state in the user data channel. linkOK - DCD line is ON only when active link is OK. on - DCD continuously ON.

prtHSClkPolarity.name: prtHSClkPolarity
prtHSClkPolarity.description: This object indicates the clock polarity.

prtHSInterfaceType.name: prtHSInterfaceType
prtHSInterfaceType.description: This object indicates the selected electrical interface type.

prtHSUnframed.name: prtHSUnframed
prtHSUnframed.description: Unframed line for HS ports. yes - means that all TSs must be transferred, including TS0. In this case, prtHSRate must be r31x56eq1736Kbps OR r31x64eq1984Kbps.

prtHSBertPrtIdx.name: prtHSBertPrtIdx
prtHSBertPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique number to identify a port. The valid port number depends on the IO slot no., the installed card type and the port type: outside, inside, SP. * The inside ports will be the HS cards ports. The convention used will be (for DXC): - first two digits will be: (IO slot number+10) - last one/two digits will be the port number within the card, in even numbers: port1 = 2 port2 = 4 port3 = 6 etc... Example: port2 of IO slot 11 will be: 214 .

prtHSBertSlt.name: prtHSBertSlt
prtHSBertSlt.description: This attribute indicates a unique number to identify the slot where the card is inserted in. When the unit is stand-alone, this object is not applicable and 255 will be used.

prtHSBertCountClr.name: prtHSBertCountClr
prtHSBertCountClr.description: Setting this object (to on) initiate bert counter clear operation. Valid only when bert test is active on the specific port. (Every time a new bert test starts, the counter is automatically cleared; this command enables clearing the counter while the test is running).

prtHSBertTestResult.name: prtHSBertTestResult
prtHSBertTestResult.description: This object indicates the number of Bit Error Rate indicated during the BERT test. Active only when bert test is running on the selected port.

prtSpCnfgEntry.name: prtSpCnfgEntry
prtSpCnfgEntry.description: All the entries at this table are identical(have the same value) at all the configurations(1..255) except at the TmpCnfg. - For products supporting more than one configuration, the write operation into the Table Objects is valid only at the TmpCnfg entry. - For products that do not support configurations, the write operation into the Table Objects will be to prtSpCnfgIdx=1.

prtSpCnfgIdx.name: prtSpCnfgIdx
prtSpCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg(1..255) being accessed. Idx of 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

prtSpPrtIdx.name: prtSpPrtIdx
prtSpPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number of the SPor DP port. For DXC, it is the port in the active DCL card: - SP = 1 - NP ; DP = 2 For Kilomux, the port index is calculated as follows: 100*Slot+Ch. For FCD, PRBi, the SP port index=1. For Optimux-T3, the SP port index=71.

prtSpUsage.name: prtSpUsage
prtSpUsage.description: This attribute indicates what is the usage of the port.

prtSpRate.name: prtSpRate
prtSpRate.description: This attribute indicates the operation rate (speed) of the port. auto - automatic rate selection, by the agent.

prtSpDataBits.name: prtSpDataBits
prtSpDataBits.description: This attribute indicates the number of data bits in async frame

prtSpParity.name: prtSpParity
prtSpParity.description: This attribute indicates the parity mode in async frame

prtSpCallOutMode.name: prtSpCallOutMode
prtSpCallOutMode.description: This attribute indicates the call-out mode. For DXC - this object is applicable only for the DP port (2).

prtSpInterface.name: prtSpInterface
prtSpInterface.description: This attribute indicates the supervisory port interface. dce - the DACS appears as a DCE for the port. dte - the DACS operates as a DTE, for connection via modem, for the port.

prtSpCTS.name: prtSpCTS
prtSpCTS.description: CTS line state. This object is applicable only for port (1) = SP

prtSpDcdDelay.name: prtSpDcdDelay
prtSpDcdDelay.description: DCD delay in msec. d10 = delay of 10msec. This object is applicable only for port (1) = SP

prtSpDsr.name: prtSpDsr
prtSpDsr.description: DSR line state. This object is applicable only for port (1) = SP

prtSpNoOfRetries.name: prtSpNoOfRetries
prtSpNoOfRetries.description: For DXC - this object is applicable only for port (2) = DP. The number of dialing retries requested. Default = 0

prtSpWaitForConnect.name: prtSpWaitForConnect
prtSpWaitForConnect.description: For DXC - this object is applicable only for port (2) = DP. Waiting time for connect, in seconds. Default = 30 sec.

prtSpDialMode.name: prtSpDialMode
prtSpDialMode.description: For DXC - this object is applicable only for port (2) = DP. Dialing mode. Default=tone

prtSpAltNumMode.name: prtSpAltNumMode
prtSpAltNumMode.description: For DXC - this object is applicable only for port (2) = DP. It determines wether to use the alternate number or not. Default = no.

prtSpPrimaryNum.name: prtSpPrimaryNum
prtSpPrimaryNum.description: For DXC - this object is applicable only for port (2) = DP. It is the Primary dialing number.

prtSpAltNum.name: prtSpAltNum
prtSpAltNum.description: For DXC - this object is applicable only for port (2) = DP. It is the Alternate dialing number. This number is applicable only if prtSpAltNumMode is 'yes'.

prtSpRoutProtocol.name: prtSpRoutProtocol
prtSpRoutProtocol.description: This attribute indicates the routing protocol of the port. notApplicable - for DP.

prtSpCmd.name: prtSpCmd
prtSpCmd.description: SP Command. For LRS this parameter will be used for a Modem Command. Upon NMS's Get operation for devices that this parameter is notApplicable, agent will send NULL string.

prtSpActCallOut.name: prtSpActCallOut
prtSpActCallOut.description: This object indicates when to Activate Call-Out. It is used by FCD-T1/E1. always - to activate call-out always. linkFail - to activate call-out only when Link of Inband Management fails.

prtSpAlrRelayMode.name: prtSpAlrRelayMode
prtSpAlrRelayMode.description: This attribute indicates the Alarm Relay Mode. notApplicable - for DP.

prtSpStopBits.name: prtSpStopBits
prtSpStopBits.description: This attribute indicates number of stop bits in an async frame.

prtDimCnfgEntry.name: prtDimCnfgEntry
prtDimCnfgEntry.description: The write operation into the Table Objects is valid only for the TmpCnfg entry (prtDimCnfgIdx=255).

prtDimCnfgIdx.name: prtDimCnfgIdx
prtDimCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg(1..255) being accessed. Idx of 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

prtDimIdx.name: prtDimIdx
prtDimIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number of the DIM card. The convention used for DXC: (IO slot number+10)*10 + 1 Example: port1 of IO slot 11 will be: 211 .

prtDimTxMode.name: prtDimTxMode
prtDimTxMode.description: Tx mode. regularTx - the links are connected to a similar outfit on the other side. In this mode, if a link fails, the transmitted bandwidth is decreased accordingly. broadcast - the links are connected to MORE than one similar outfit on the other side. In this mode, if a link fails, the transmitted bandwidth is not affected

prtDimClkMode.name: prtDimClkMode
prtDimClkMode.description: Clock Mode. smooth - a clock that is not 'pulsed'(has no 'gaps'). In this mode the DXC does NOT receive back the clock signal. extSmooth - same as 'smooth' but in this mode, the DXC receives back the clock signal.

prtDimMaxDelay.name: prtDimMaxDelay
prtDimMaxDelay.description: Max Delay permitted between the links, in msec.

prtDimMng.name: prtDimMng
prtDimMng.description: Use of DIM port for management. disabled - no management on DIM ts1 - 1 bit of TS1 is used for management.

prtDimMngRoutProt.name: prtDimMngRoutProt
prtDimMngRoutProt.description: Mng Routing Protocol of the port. none - when prtDimMng is 'disabled'.

prtDimDestEntry.name: prtDimDestEntry
prtDimDestEntry.description: The write operation is valid only for the TmpCnfg entry (prtDimDestCnfgIdx=255).

prtDestCnfgIdx.name: prtDestCnfgIdx
prtDestCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg(1..255) being accessed. Idx of 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

prtDestDimIdx.name: prtDestDimIdx
prtDestDimIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number of the DIM card. The convention used for DXC: (IO slot number+10) & 1 Example: port1 of IO slot 11 will be: 211 .

prtDestIdx.name: prtDestIdx
prtDestIdx.description: This attribute indicates a destination number of the DIM card.

prtDest.name: prtDest
prtDest.description: Destination port,(of a T1/E1 port), that is connected to the DIM card, for the specified Destination number. 0 = No destination port. Else: For external ports: (IO Slot+10) & 1 for port 1 (IO Slot+10) & 3 for port 2 Example: port2 of IO slot 12 will be: 223 . For internal ports : (IO Slot+10) & 2 for port 1 (IO Slot+10) & 4 for port 2 (IO Slot+10) & 6 for port 3 (IO Slot+10) & 8 for port 4, etc...

prtDestConnect.name: prtDestConnect
prtDestConnect.description: Connection Status of the specified destination number. For a specified destination port, it depends both on the status of the port and on the status of the far-end port. Since this is a RO object, same value will be received for all configurations.

prtICnfgIdx.name: prtICnfgIdx
prtICnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Config being accessed. Idx of 255 relates to the Temporary (Scratch) Config.

prtIIdx.name: prtIIdx
prtIIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique number to identify a port. The valid port number depends on the IO slot no., the installed card type and the port type: outside, inside, SP. * The ISDN B1, B2, D channels will be inside ports. For port index, see product specification.

prtIRate.name: prtIRate
prtIRate.description: This object indicates the port rate in bits. Each TS contains 8 bits. Thus, 1 bit is equivalent to 8Kbps rate.

prtIConnect.name: prtIConnect
prtIConnect.description: D channel connection. no - disconnected yes - connected.

prtHdslIdx.name: prtHdslIdx
prtHdslIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique number to identify a port. The valid port number depends on the IO slot no., the installed card type and the port type: outside, inside. * The HDSL ports will be external. For port index, see product specification.

prtHdslMode.name: prtHdslMode
prtHdslMode.description: This object indicates the HDSL mode.

prtHdslRptrType.name: prtHdslRptrType
prtHdslRptrType.description: The Repeater between Near and Far modem. none - no repeater exists between the modems hrpt - HRPT repeater exists between the modems.

prtHdslMaxRate.name: prtHdslMaxRate
prtHdslMaxRate.description: Maximum Rate of the xDSL Line, in Kbps units. This object can be Set only for a Central unit.

prtHdslLinkType.name: prtHdslLinkType
prtHdslLinkType.description: The Link Type. msdsl2w - MSDSL 2 Wire hdsl2w - HDSL 2 Wire hdsl4w - HDSL 4 Wire gDsl - G.DSL

prtHdslCompSwVer.name: prtHdslCompSwVer
prtHdslCompSwVer.description: This object indicates the Software Version of the component (Piggyback card) supporting this interface.

prtHdslCompHwVer.name: prtHdslCompHwVer
prtHdslCompHwVer.description: This object indicates the Hardware Version of the component (Piggyback card) supporting this interface.

prtT3E3CnfgEntry.name: prtT3E3CnfgEntry
prtT3E3CnfgEntry.description: An entry in the T3/E3 port configuration table.

prtT3E3CnfgIdx.name: prtT3E3CnfgIdx
prtT3E3CnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Config being accessed. Idx of 255 relates to the Temporary (Scratch) Config. For DXC, write operations can be performed only on the Temp Config. For products that do not support configurations, always 1 will be used.

prtT3E3PrtIdx.name: prtT3E3PrtIdx
prtT3E3PrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number. For DXC: The same numbering as for prtGenPrtIdx. The valid port number depends on the IO slot no., the installed card type and the port type: outside, inside. * The external ports convention used will be (for DXC): - first two digits will be: (IO slot number+10) - last one/two digits will be the port number within the card, in odd numbers: port1 = 1 port2 = 3 port3 = 5 etc... Example: port2 of IO slot 11 will be: 213 . For Optimux-T3: Link-A: 51 Link-B: 61 .

prtT3E3Slt.name: prtT3E3Slt
prtT3E3Slt.description: This attribute indicates a unique number to identify the slot where the card is inserted in. When the unit is stand-alone, this object is not applicable and 255 will be used.

prtT3E3LineLength.name: prtT3E3LineLength
prtT3E3LineLength.description: This object is the length of the ds3 line in feet. It provides information for line build out circuitry if it exists and can use this object to adjust the line build out. len0p450ft = 0 - 450 feet len451p900ft = 451 - 900 feet.

prtT3E3InbandMng.name: prtT3E3InbandMng
prtT3E3InbandMng.description: A unique number to identify the Frame Type over the link. For Optimux-T3: only values (4), (7) are supported.

prtT3E3AisFrame.name: prtT3E3AisFrame
prtT3E3AisFrame.description: This object is applicable only for Optimux-T3. It allows user to select whether the AIS sent will be framed or unframed.

prtT3E3RoutProt.name: prtT3E3RoutProt
prtT3E3RoutProt.description: Routing Protocol of the port. This object is applicable only for T3 ports.

prtT3E3AisTransmit.name: prtT3E3AisTransmit
prtT3E3AisTransmit.description: Indicates if AIS signal will be transmitted over the tributary E3/DS3 upon failure.

cmprTypeIdx.name: cmprTypeIdx
cmprTypeIdx.description: This object indicates the Type of the Compressed data referred (which table, which level, etc). The type is a code according to a convention between agent and NMS.

cmprCnfgIdx.name: cmprCnfgIdx
cmprCnfgIdx.description: This object indicates the configuration number the Compressed information relates to.

cmprVersion.name: cmprVersion
cmprVersion.description: This object indicates the version of the internal format of the Compressed data (the version of the convention used).

cmprSltIdx.name: cmprSltIdx
cmprSltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique number of the slot position where the card is inserted. When the unit is stand-alone or this object is not applicable, 255 will be used.

cmprPrtIdx.name: cmprPrtIdx
cmprPrtIdx.description: This object indicates a unique identifier of the port, the compressed information relates to. For DXC - according to the order in the card of cmprSltIdx: - first two digits will be: (IO slot number+10) - last one/two digits will be the port number within the card in odd or even numbers, as follows: * For the outside/external ports, in odd numbers: port1 = 1 port2 = 3 port3 = 5 etc... Example: port2 of IO slot 11 will be: 213 . * The inside/internal ports, in even numbers: port1 = 2 port2 = 4 port3 = 6 etc... Example: port2 of IO slot 11 will be: 214 . For FCD: see product's specification. If the port number is irrelevant to this parameter (if it is a system/card level alarm) the value will be 9999.

cmprObj.name: cmprObj
cmprObj.description: This object is the compressed information itself, according to a predefined format, both agent and NMS agreed about.

mapLinkIdx.name: mapLinkIdx
mapLinkIdx.description: A unique identifier of the link

mapLinkSlotIdx.name: mapLinkSlotIdx
mapLinkSlotIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the module is inserted.

mapLinkPortIdx.name: mapLinkPortIdx
mapLinkPortIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number. The valid port number depends on the IO slot no., the installed card type and the port type: outside, inside, SP. In the DXC : - first two digits will be: (IO slot number+10) - last one/two digits will be the port number within the card in odd or even numbers, as follows: * For the outside/external ports, in odd numbers: port1 = 1 port2 = 3 port3 = 5 etc... Example: port2 of IO slot 11 will be: 213 . * The inside/internal ports, in even numbers: port1 = 2 port2 = 4 port3 = 6 etc... Example: port2 of IO slot 11 will be: 214 .

mapLinkState.name: mapLinkState
mapLinkState.description: This attribute indicates the status of the link between the two muxes

alrGenCode.name: alrGenCode
alrGenCode.description: This object is a unique code number, identifying a certain alarm.

alrGenDescription.name: alrGenDescription
alrGenDescription.description: This entry is a unique text description, of the alarm corresponding to the specified code.

alrGenSlotType.name: alrGenSlotType
alrGenSlotType.description: Slot type that the alarm is relevant to. clAndIo - an alarm that is relevant for both CL and IO slots.

alrGenSeverity.name: alrGenSeverity
alrGenSeverity.description: This object enables the user to select a severity for each alarm. The severity is set per alarm code (same for all slots/ports using this code).

alrGenDebounce.name: alrGenDebounce
alrGenDebounce.description: Debounce time for each alarm code, in seconds. The meaning is, that an alarm will be 'declared' as ON (or OFF), only after it was actually ON/OFF the Debouncing time selected by user. 0 = default debounce selection (each alarm has a default value). 250 = maximum value of seconds for debounce. 253 = mask = the alarm will Never be reported. 254 = default debounce selection (each alarm has a default value). 255 = not applicable

alrGenDefSeverity.name: alrGenDefSeverity
alrGenDefSeverity.description: This object reports the default severity of each alarm. User can change the severity of the alarms defined by this default via the alrGenSeverity object.

sanityCheckTrap.name: sanityCheckTrap
sanityCheckTrap.description: This trap is sent after a data base download attempt. It returns the sanity result status and the configuration no.checked.

dacsMuxAlarmsTrap.name: dacsMuxAlarmsTrap
dacsMuxAlarmsTrap.description: This trap is sent when an alarm occurs.

mdlConnectTrap.name: mdlConnectTrap
mdlConnectTrap.description: This trap is sent when a card is removed.

sysAlrStatusTrap.name: sysAlrStatusTrap
sysAlrStatusTrap.description: This trap is sent upon any change in the value of any of the variables.

sysStatusChangedTrap.name: sysStatusChangedTrap
sysStatusChangedTrap.description: This trap is sent when Leds status is changed.

cnfgUpdateTrap.name: cnfgUpdateTrap
cnfgUpdateTrap.description: This trap is sent upon change of the active Configuration DB.

ethIfIdx.name: ethIfIdx
ethIfIdx.description: A unique index of the ethernet interface/port.

ethMode.name: ethMode
ethMode.description: This object indicates the Ethernet mode of operation.

ethBridgingMode.name: ethBridgingMode
ethBridgingMode.description: This object indicates the bridging mode of the Ethernet interface.

ethEncapsulationCRCMode.name: ethEncapsulationCRCMode
ethEncapsulationCRCMode.description: This object define the encapsulation type requested for the Ethernet interface. It indicates if we transfer the Ethernet frame to the other side with or without the CRC.

ethBackPressure.name: ethBackPressure
ethBackPressure.description: This parameter defines whether to enable or disable Back pressure. Back Pressure is a flow control parameter.

ethLimit4.name: ethLimit4
ethLimit4.description: This parameter determine the Back off algorithm mode. Every 4 following collisions the Framer will be thrown out (4 times more than usuall).

ethSkipInitReset.name: ethSkipInitReset
ethSkipInitReset.description: This parameter defines whether read status on reset.

ethMulticastBlock.name: ethMulticastBlock
ethMulticastBlock.description: This parameter defines whether to send multicast message to WAN from LAN or not.

ethBroadcastBlock.name: ethBroadcastBlock
ethBroadcastBlock.description: This parameter defines whether to send broadcast message to WAN from LAN or not.

ethSpeed.name: ethSpeed
ethSpeed.description: This parameter defines the line speed.

ethRip2.name: ethRip2
ethRip2.description: This parameter defines whether to send RIP II message to WAN from LAN or not

ethPortPriority.name: ethPortPriority
ethPortPriority.description: This parameter defines if priority is to be considered for this Port.

ethPortMngEnable.name: ethPortMngEnable
ethPortMngEnable.description: This parameter defines whether management data can pass through this Port.

ethFlowCtrlMacAddress.name: ethFlowCtrlMacAddress
ethFlowCtrlMacAddress.description: In case of flow control - transmit frame with this specific MAC address to inform the other end to stop sending frames. Default: 01.80.C2.00.00.01.

ethIfCurrentEntry.name: ethIfCurrentEntry
ethIfCurrentEntry.description: An entry in the Ethernet Current table.

ethIfCurrentIndex.name: ethIfCurrentIndex
ethIfCurrentIndex.description: The index of the Ethernet interface. It may be ifIndex.

ethIfCurrentStatus.name: ethIfCurrentStatus
ethIfCurrentStatus.description: The statuses of the current interval: 0 - Valid. 1 - redundantLinkSwitch - the link has been switched by a redundancy mechanism. 2 - discontinuity - module was partialy out. 4 - notValid - module is out.

ethIfCurrentInFrames.name: ethIfCurrentInFrames
ethIfCurrentInFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of received frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current 15 minute interval.

ethIfCurrentInOctets.name: ethIfCurrentInOctets
ethIfCurrentInOctets.description: The counter associated with the number of received octets, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current 15 minute interval.

ethIfCurrentAlignmentErrors.name: ethIfCurrentAlignmentErrors
ethIfCurrentAlignmentErrors.description: The counter associated with the number of received frames, which are not complete (The result of dividing the number of bits by 8 is not an Integer), encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current 15 minute interval.

ethIfCurrentFCSErrors.name: ethIfCurrentFCSErrors
ethIfCurrentFCSErrors.description: The counter associated with the number of received frames that didn't pass the FCS test, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current 15 minute interval.

ethIfCurrentLengthError.name: ethIfCurrentLengthError
ethIfCurrentLengthError.description: The counter associated with the number of received frames with length error, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current 15 minute interval.

ethIfCurrentOutFrames.name: ethIfCurrentOutFrames
ethIfCurrentOutFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current 15 minute interval.

ethIfCurrentOutOctets.name: ethIfCurrentOutOctets
ethIfCurrentOutOctets.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted octets, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current 15 minute interval.

ethIfCurrentSingleCollisionFrames.name: ethIfCurrentSingleCollisionFrames
ethIfCurrentSingleCollisionFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of successfully transmitted frames for which transmission was inhibited by exactly one collision, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current 15 minute interval.

ethIfCurrentMultipleCollisionFrames.name: ethIfCurrentMultipleCollisionFrames
ethIfCurrentMultipleCollisionFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of successfully transmitted frames for which transmission was inhibited by more than one collision, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current 15 minute interval.

ethIfCurrentDeferredTransmissions.name: ethIfCurrentDeferredTransmissions
ethIfCurrentDeferredTransmissions.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted frames for which the first transmission attempt was delayed due to a busy media, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current 15 minute interval.

ethIfCurrentLateCollisions.name: ethIfCurrentLateCollisions
ethIfCurrentLateCollisions.description: The counter associated with the number of times that a collision was detected later than the first 64 bytes of the frame, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current 15 minute interval.

ethIfCurrentCarrierSenseErrors.name: ethIfCurrentCarrierSenseErrors
ethIfCurrentCarrierSenseErrors.description: The counter associated with the number of times that the carrier sense condition was lost or never asserted when attempting to transmit a frame, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current 15 minute interval.

ethIfCurrentInputCongestionDropped.name: ethIfCurrentInputCongestionDropped
ethIfCurrentInputCongestionDropped.description: The counter associated with the number of frames dropped due to lack of buffers in ingress pool, encountered by the Ethernet interface in the current 15 minute interval.

ethIfCurrentOutputCongestionDropped.name: ethIfCurrentOutputCongestionDropped
ethIfCurrentOutputCongestionDropped.description: The counter associated with the number of dropped frames due to a congestion, encountered by the Transmit direction to the Ethernet interface in the current 15 minute interval.

ethIfIntervalEntry.name: ethIfIntervalEntry
ethIfIntervalEntry.description: An entry in the Ethernet Interval table.

ethIfIntervalIndex.name: ethIfIntervalIndex
ethIfIntervalIndex.description: The index of the Ethernet interface. It may be ifIndex.

ethIfIntervalNumber.name: ethIfIntervalNumber
ethIfIntervalNumber.description: A number between 1 and 96, where 1 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval and 96 is the least recently completed 15 minutes interval (assuming that all 96 intervals exist).

ethIfIntervalStatus.name: ethIfIntervalStatus
ethIfIntervalStatus.description: The statuses of the current interval: 0 - Valid. 1 - redundantLinkSwitch - the link has been switched by a redundancy mechanism. 2 - discontinuity - module was partialy out. 4 - notValid - module is out.

ethIfIntervalInFrames.name: ethIfIntervalInFrames
ethIfIntervalInFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of received frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

ethIfIntervalInOctets.name: ethIfIntervalInOctets
ethIfIntervalInOctets.description: The counter associated with the number of received octets, encountered by the Ethernet interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

ethIfIntervalAlignmentErrors.name: ethIfIntervalAlignmentErrors
ethIfIntervalAlignmentErrors.description: The counter associated with the number of received frames, which are not complete (The result of dividing the number of bits by 8 is not an Integer), encountered by the Ethernet interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

ethIfIntervalFCSErrors.name: ethIfIntervalFCSErrors
ethIfIntervalFCSErrors.description: The counter associated with the number of received frames that didn't pass the FCS test, encountered by the Ethernet interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

ethIfIntervalLengthError.name: ethIfIntervalLengthError
ethIfIntervalLengthError.description: The counter associated with the number of received frames with length error, encountered by the Ethernet interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

ethIfIntervalOutFrames.name: ethIfIntervalOutFrames
ethIfIntervalOutFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

ethIfIntervalOutOctets.name: ethIfIntervalOutOctets
ethIfIntervalOutOctets.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted octets, encountered by the Ethernet interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

ethIfIntervalSingleCollisionFrames.name: ethIfIntervalSingleCollisionFrames
ethIfIntervalSingleCollisionFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of successfully transmitted frames for which transmission was inhibited by exactly one collision, encountered by the Ethernet interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

ethIfIntervalMultipleCollisionFrames.name: ethIfIntervalMultipleCollisionFrames
ethIfIntervalMultipleCollisionFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of successfully transmitted frames for which transmission was inhibited by more than one collision, encountered by the Ethernet interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

ethIfIntervalDeferredTransmissions.name: ethIfIntervalDeferredTransmissions
ethIfIntervalDeferredTransmissions.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted frames for which the first transmission attempt was delayed due to a busy media, encountered by the Ethernet interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

ethIfIntervalLateCollisions.name: ethIfIntervalLateCollisions
ethIfIntervalLateCollisions.description: The counter associated with the number of times that a collision was detected later than the first 64 bytes of the frame, encountered by the Ethernet interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

ethIfIntervalCarrierSenseErrors.name: ethIfIntervalCarrierSenseErrors
ethIfIntervalCarrierSenseErrors.description: The counter associated with the number of times that the carrier sense condition was lost or never asserted when attempting to transmit a frame, encountered by the Ethernet interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

ethIfIntervalInputCongestionDropped.name: ethIfIntervalInputCongestionDropped
ethIfIntervalInputCongestionDropped.description: The counter associated with the number of dropped frames due to a congestion, encountered by the Receive direction to the Ethernet interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

ethIfIntervalOutputCongestionDropped.name: ethIfIntervalOutputCongestionDropped
ethIfIntervalOutputCongestionDropped.description: The counter associated with the number of dropped frames due to a congestion, encountered by the Transmit direction to the Ethernet interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

ethPerformanceMode.name: ethPerformanceMode
ethPerformanceMode.description: This object indicates whether OK or Fail statistics will be counted.

ethIfPerfEntry.name: ethIfPerfEntry
ethIfPerfEntry.description: An entry in the Ethernet Performance table.

ethIfPerfInOkFrames.name: ethIfPerfInOkFrames
ethIfPerfInOkFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of received OK frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface since ethPerformanceMode Set to countOK (2) or Reset Statistics was done.

ethIfPerfOutOkFrames.name: ethIfPerfOutOkFrames
ethIfPerfOutOkFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted OK frames, encountered by the Ethernet interface since ethPerformanceMode Set to countOK (2) or Reset Statistics was done.

ethIfPerfTotalCollisions.name: ethIfPerfTotalCollisions
ethIfPerfTotalCollisions.description: The counter associated with the total number of collisions of any type encountered by the Ethernet interface since ethPerformanceMode Set to countOK (2) or Reset Statistics was done

optMxConfigTable.name: optMxConfigTable
optMxConfigTable.description: This table contains parameters of configuration for each member of the couple of Optimux.

optMxConfigEntry.name: optMxConfigEntry
optMxConfigEntry.description: An entry in the Optimux Config table.

optIndex.name: optIndex
optIndex.description: optIndex = 1 is for local Optimux. optIndex = 2 is for remote Optimux.

optPSPrimary.name: optPSPrimary
optPSPrimary.description: The status of the primary Power Supply Unit.

optPSSecondary.name: optPSSecondary
optPSSecondary.description: The status of the secondary Power Supply Unit.

optLinkActive.name: optLinkActive
optLinkActive.description: This object indicates which link is active. For Optimux-4 it may be: 5, 6 or 105, 106 For FOMi-E3/T3 it may be: 51, 61 or 151, 161. For Optimux-T3 it may be: 51 or 61. For Optimux-155/1 refer to product spec.

optSelectLink.name: optSelectLink
optSelectLink.description: This object is used by Optimux 4E1/T1 and Optimux-T3. - For Optimux 4E1/T1: This MIB object enables the user to force the device to use specific link. autoredundancy= Main (Link 1) is the default link. When it will fail, the device will use Backup (Link 2). If Main recovers, it automatically returns to Main. autoWoReturn = Automatic Without Return. Main (Link 1) is the default link. When it will fail, the device will use Backup (Link 2). If Main recovers, it will NOT return to Main. It will continue using Backup. This option is supported only by LRS cards. main = Forces the device to start immediately use of Main (Link 1), no matter what is its state and stay there. No Redundancy. back = Forces the device to start immediately use of Backup (Link 2), no matter what is its state and stay there. No Redundancy. - For Optimux-T3 and Optimux-155/1: This MIB object is used to select which Link will be used as MAIN. Therefore: autoredundancy - not supported main = Link A is MAIN (=default). back = Link B is MAIN.

optGrpPayLoadLoop.name: optGrpPayLoadLoop
optGrpPayLoadLoop.description: Performs payload loop ( remote loop) to 4 E1 channels at once.

optGrpClockSource.name: optGrpClockSource
optGrpClockSource.description: For Optimux XL: If dsx3TransmitClockSource = localTiming(2), then the user can configure this field as: localInternal(2) = use the internal clock of the device localExternal(3) = use the external clock connected to the port dedicated to clock. For FomiE3/T3 this object is always applicable. localExternal(3) = station clock transparent(5) = the device takes the clock info from the data. For FomiE3/T3 with HSSI electrical interface, only the following are valid: localInternal(2) and transparent(5). For Optimux-T3 the applicable values are (2), (3), (4). For Optimux-155/1 the applicable values are (2), (3), (4), (5).

optRedundancyStatus.name: optRedundancyStatus
optRedundancyStatus.description: If there are two modules 'links', then this field should be set to available(2). If there is only one module 'link', this field should be set to notAvailable(3).

optRedundancyCnf.name: optRedundancyCnf
optRedundancyCnf.description: This object is used by Optimux-XL, FomiE3/T3, Optimux-T3 and Optimux-155/1. For Optimux-XL: If optRedundancyStatus = notAvailable(3), then this field can be off(2) or forcedBU(6). - off(2) = forcedMain: forces the device to start immediately use of Main (Link 1), no matter what is its state and stay there - forcedBU(6) = forces the device to start immediately use of Backup (Link 2), no matter what is its state and stay there. This value is not supported by Optimux-T3. Else, user can configure this field as: auto(3) = switch back to main link when valid. manual(4) = don't switch back to main link = automatic w/o return. For FomiE3/T3 all values are applicable unconditioned. For Optimux-T3, values off(2), auto(3), manual(4) are applicable unconditioned. For Optimux-155/1 values off (2) = Protection Lockout, auto (3) and manual (4)

optFarEndType.name: optFarEndType
optFarEndType.description: Far-End type of product. This object is especially relevant for the local optimux. optimux4Sa (2), optimux4Card(3),optimux4E1L (8), optimux4T1L (9) - are relevant only for Optimux-4E1/T1 cards. notApplicable - for devices that don't have a far-end unit.

optServiceChEnable.name: optServiceChEnable
optServiceChEnable.description: Service Channel Enable/Disable for each Optimux (local/remote). This object is applicable only for Optimux cards.

optMaskChAlr.name: optMaskChAlr
optMaskChAlr.description: Mask Channel Alarm. This object is applicable only for Optimux cards. The value of this object is a sum of 2**n, where n is a bit assigned to a certain Channel. For Optimux-4: Bit0: CH1 ; Bit1: CH2 ; Bit2: CH3 ; Bit3: CH4 (Bit='1' means masked). Examples: - 15 : means that all Channels are masked. - 9 : means that Alarms of CH 1 and CH 4 are masked. For Optimux-T3: Bit0: CH1 ; Bit1: CH2 ; Bit2: CH3 ;.. Bit20: CH21 OR Bit27: CH28 (Bit='1' means masked).

optAisEnable.name: optAisEnable
optAisEnable.description: AIS enable/disable. notApplicable - for devices that do not support this feature.

optFarMng.name: optFarMng
optFarMng.description: This object is used by Optimux-XL and FomiE3/T3. Is there possibility of Far-End Management (no/yes). This object is applicable only for the Local device. notApplicable - for Remote device and devices that do not support it. no - far-end device is NOT I-Type so it doesn't have a management link to its pair-device. yes - far-end device is I-Type so it has a management link to its pair-device.

optClockDivision.name: optClockDivision
optClockDivision.description: This object is applicable only for FomiE3/T3 having an HSSI Electrical interface. It gives the possibility of Clock Division, so that Clock Rate will be less than T3/E3. notApplicable - for a device that does not support it noDivision - Clock stays as is (Internal or Transparent) half - Clock will be half the original (divided by 2) quarter - Clock will be a quarter of the original (divided by 4).

optDteLoopEnable.name: optDteLoopEnable
optDteLoopEnable.description: DTE Loop enable/disable (for example loop command requested by router). This object is applicable only for products having HSSI interface. notApplicable - for devices that do not support this feature.

optGrpClockSourcePrt.name: optGrpClockSourcePrt
optGrpClockSourcePrt.description: This object is applicable for Optimux-T3, when optGrpClockSource=localExternal. It enables the user to select the Channel or Station Clock from which the Clock is received. Valid values: 0 = notApplicable 1..28 (= CH1..CH28). 73 = Station Clock. Only T1 Channels can be used as Clock Source. For Optimux-155/1 refer to product spec for port indexing.

optIncomingAlarm.name: optIncomingAlarm
optIncomingAlarm.description: State of the Incoming Alarm (On/Off), via Alarm Relay connector. This object is applicable only for Optimux-T3.

optDefChannelSet.name: optDefChannelSet
optDefChannelSet.description: Default configuration for all Optimux Channels: T1 or E1. This object is applicable only for Optimux-T3.

optWaitToRestore.name: optWaitToRestore
optWaitToRestore.description: This parameter defines the time (sec) device has to wait in the redundant state until it goes back to the default Link.

optEnforcedLink.name: optEnforcedLink
optEnforcedLink.description: This parameter is not applicable when optRedundancyCnf = off. It enables user to enforce a Link in spite of the redundancy mechanism. Selecting the noEnforcement(2) value cause return to the usual rules of the redundancy mechanism. main (3) and backup (4) are unconditional (force).

optFlipUponEvent.name: optFlipUponEvent
optFlipUponEvent.description: This object allows user to define if Flip to the other port will be performed (or not), for certain possible events. Each event is represented by a bit. The value of the object is a sum of 2**n, according to the bits having '1' value. '1' - means that Flip should occur due to this event. Bit 0 (LSB) = SD (Signal Degraded).

optHwMaskChAlr.name: optHwMaskChAlr
optHwMaskChAlr.description: Mask Channel Alarm done by the HW dip-switches. This object is applicable only for Optimux cards. The value of this object is a sum of 2**n, where n is a bit assigned to a certain Channel. For Optimux-16E1: Bit0: CH1 ; Bit1: CH2 ; Bit2: CH3 ;.. Bit15: CH16 (Bit='1' means masked). Examples: - 9 : means that Alarms of CH 1 and CH 4 are masked.

For FomiE3/R3: Slot of Station Clock = 3, Slot of Electrical Link = 4, Slot of Optical Main Link = 5, Slot of Optical Backup Link = 6 . For Optimux-T3: Slot of Station Clock (internal card)= 3, Slot A = 5, Slot B = 6. For Optimux-155/1: E1/T1 Slot A - 1, E1/T1 Slot B- 2, LINK-A - 5, LINK-B - 6 I/O-1 - 11, I/O-2 -12 ...I/O-6 - 16 For Optimux-155 DS3: Common Logic+E3/T3 Slot A - 1, Common Logic+E3/T3 Slot B- 2, LINK-A - 5, LINK-B - 6

prtSonetGenIdx.name: prtSonetGenIdx
prtSonetGenIdx.description: This object indicates a unique port or interface number. For numbering, see product's spec. For some products, the numbering can equal ifIndex.

prtSonetGenSdThreshold.name: prtSonetGenSdThreshold
prtSonetGenSdThreshold.description: SD=Signal Degraded Threshold. Units: [10E-]. The threshold is 10E-x relative to the frequency of the data flow. x=3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9. n3= 10E-3 n4= 10E-4 n5= 10E-5 n6= 10E-6 n7= 10E-7 n8= 10E-8 n9= 10E-9 .

prtSonetGenEedThreshold.name: prtSonetGenEedThreshold

prtSonetGenBerEnable.name: prtSonetGenBerEnable
prtSonetGenBerEnable.description: Controls the activation of the Line Ber (Bit Error Rate), means whether SD and EED threshold parameters will be enabled.

prtSonetStm1Entry.name: prtSonetStm1Entry
prtSonetStm1Entry.description: An entry in the Sonet/SDH STM-1 port configuration table.

prtSonetVcJRxPathTraceEnable.name: prtSonetVcJRxPathTraceEnable
prtSonetVcJRxPathTraceEnable.description: Enable/Disable checking Jy Path Trace. y=1, 2: J1 - for VC-4 layer J2 - for VC-12 layer.

prtSonetXConnectConPrtIdx.description: This object indicates the connected port. For port numbering, see product's spec. For some products, the numbering can equal ifIndex. notApplicable - will be indicated as 255.

prtSonetXConnectTUG3Idx.name: prtSonetXConnectTUG3Idx
prtSonetXConnectTUG3Idx.description: This object indicates a TUG-3 (Tributary Unit Group 3) within VC-4. The valid TUG3s are values are 1..3. and 255 which designates NA

prtSonetXConnectTUG2Idx.name: prtSonetXConnectTUG2Idx
prtSonetXConnectTUG2Idx.description: This object indicates a TUG2 (Tributary Unit Group 2 ) within VC-3. The valid TUG2's values are 1..7 and 255 which designates NA

prtSonetXConnectTUnIdx.description: This object indicates a TUn within TUG-2 or TUG-3 (Tributary Unit n, where n is 2, 12 or 11 within TUG-2, or 3 within TUG-3) valid values are 1 for TU-2 1 for TU-3 1..4 for TU-11 1..3 for TU-12 255 designates NA

vcGroupCnfgVcType.description: User may select type of SDH Virtual Containers (VC) (SONET Virtual Tributaries VT ) to be concatenated in this Virtual Concatenation Group. For SDH, values 2,3,4 are valid. For SONET, values 5 and 6 are valid.

vcGroupCnfgNoOfVCs.name: vcGroupCnfgNoOfVCs

vcGroupCnfgGroupIfIndex.description: The ifIndex assigend to this group.

vcGroupCnfgGfpChId.name: vcGroupCnfgGfpChId
vcGroupCnfgGfpChId.description: Generic Framing Procedure (GFP) Channel ID, Valid only when vcGroupCnfgEncapsulation = gfp (4) Valid values are 0x00 - oxFF (hex)

vcgGfpMuxCnfgEntry.description: An entry in the Virtual Concatenation Group GFP Mux configuration table.

vcgGfpMuxCnfgIdx.description: This object indicates the Index of the configuration being accessed. Index of 255 relates to the Temporary (Scratch) coninguration. For products that support several configurations, Set can be performed only to the Temporary Config (=255).

vcgGfpMuxCnfgMuxNumber.name: vcgGfpMuxCnfgMuxNumber

vcgGfpMuxCnfgMuxName.description: Virtual Concatenation Group, GFP Mux name.

vcgGfpMuxCnfgGrpBwAlloc.name: vcgGfpMuxCnfgGrpBwAlloc

Other VCGs may be secondaries. VCG with allocated BW value of zero does not belong to the GFPmux defined by GFP Mux number. ________________________________________ | Octet 0 | Octet 1 | |Nibble 4 Nibble 3| Nibble 2| Nibble 1| MSB | 7 6 5 4 | 3 2 1 0 | 7 6 5 4 | 3 2 1 0 | LSB VCG1 VCG2 VCG 3 VCG4 Nibble value - BW Percentage (0...7) (0 ...87.5%) 1 0001 12.5 % 2 0010 25% 3 0011 37.5 ..... 7 0111 87.5% at least one nibble must be greater that zero. Sum of alloacted BW must be 100%. Primary VCG BW must be greater than zero.
