prtDs3CurrentPlcpBIP.description: The counter associated with the number of BIP errors, encountered by a DS3 interface in the current 15 minute interval. This counter is relevant for PLCP (external/internal) frame types only.

prtDs3CurrentPlcpFEBE.name: prtDs3CurrentPlcpFEBE
prtDs3CurrentPlcpFEBE.description: The counter associated with the number of FEBE errors, encountered by a DS3 interface in the current 15 minute interval. This counter is relevant for PLCP (external/internal) frame types only.

prtDs3CurrentBPV.name: prtDs3CurrentBPV
prtDs3CurrentBPV.description: Number of BPVs (Bi-Polar Violations) , encountered by a DS3 interface in the current 15 minute interval. This object is relevant only for Electrical Line of Fomi-E3/T3.

prtDs3CurrentLCE.name: prtDs3CurrentLCE
prtDs3CurrentLCE.description: Number of LCE (Link Code Errors) encountered by a DS3 interface in the current 15 minute interval. This object is relevant only for Optical Links of Fomi-E3/T3.

prtDs3CurrentStatus.name: prtDs3CurrentStatus
prtDs3CurrentStatus.description: The statuses of the current interval: 0 - Valid. 1 - redundantLinkSwitch - the link has been switched by a redundancy mechanism. 2 - discontinuity - module was partialy out. 4 - notValid - module is out.

prtDs3IntervalEntry.name: prtDs3IntervalEntry
prtDs3IntervalEntry.description: An entry in the DS3 Interval table.

prtDs3IntervalNumber.name: prtDs3IntervalNumber
prtDs3IntervalNumber.description: A number between 1 and 96, where 1 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval and 96 is the least recently completed 15 minutes interval (assuming that all 96 intervals are valid).

prtDs3IntervalLOS.name: prtDs3IntervalLOS
prtDs3IntervalLOS.description: The counter associated with the number of LOS seconds , encountered by a DS3 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

prtDs3IntervalOOF.name: prtDs3IntervalOOF
prtDs3IntervalOOF.description: The counter associated with the number of OOF seconds, encountered by a DS3 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

prtDs3IntervalLOC.name: prtDs3IntervalLOC
prtDs3IntervalLOC.description: The counter associated with the number of LOC seconds, encountered by a DS3 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

prtDs3IntervalAIS.name: prtDs3IntervalAIS
prtDs3IntervalAIS.description: The counter associated with the number of AIS seconds, encountered by a SONET interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

prtDs3IntervalRDI.name: prtDs3IntervalRDI
prtDs3IntervalRDI.description: The counter associated with the number of RDI seconds, encountered by a DS3 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

prtDs3IntervalUAS.name: prtDs3IntervalUAS
prtDs3IntervalUAS.description: The counter associated with the number of UAS, encountered by a DS3 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

prtDs3IntervalBIP.name: prtDs3IntervalBIP
prtDs3IntervalBIP.description: The counter associated with the number of BIP errors, encountered by a DS3 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

prtDs3IntervalFEBE.name: prtDs3IntervalFEBE
prtDs3IntervalFEBE.description: The counter associated with the number of FEBE errors, encountered by a DS3 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

prtDs3IntervalSLM.name: prtDs3IntervalSLM
prtDs3IntervalSLM.description: The counter associated with the number of SLM seconds, encountered by an E3 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

prtDs3IntervalSES.name: prtDs3IntervalSES
prtDs3IntervalSES.description: The counter associated with the number of SES encountered by a E3 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

prtDs3IntervalES.name: prtDs3IntervalES
prtDs3IntervalES.description: The number of Errored Seconds, encountered by a DS3 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

prtDs3IntervalBitParity.name: prtDs3IntervalBitParity
prtDs3IntervalBitParity.description: Bit Parity Error counter. Relevant to T3 only.

prtDs3IntervalPlcpLOF.name: prtDs3IntervalPlcpLOF
prtDs3IntervalPlcpLOF.description: The counter associated with the number of LOF seconds, encountered by a DS3 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals. This counter is relevant for plcpInternal(5) or plcpExternal(6) configuration If frame types only.

prtDs3IntervalPlcpRAI.name: prtDs3IntervalPlcpRAI
prtDs3IntervalPlcpRAI.description: Receiving Yellow/Remote Alarm Indication. This counter is relevant for PLCP (external/internal) frame types only.

prtDs3IntervalPlcpBIP.name: prtDs3IntervalPlcpBIP
prtDs3IntervalPlcpBIP.description: The counter associated with the number of BIP errors, encountered by a DS3 interface in the current 15 minute interval. This counter is relevant for PLCP (external/internal) frame types only.

prtDs3IntervalPlcpFEBE.name: prtDs3IntervalPlcpFEBE
prtDs3IntervalPlcpFEBE.description: The counter associated with the number of FEBE errors, encountered by a DS3 interface in the current 15 minute interval. This counter is relevant for PLCP (external/internal) frame types only.

prtDs3IntervalBPV.name: prtDs3IntervalBPV
prtDs3IntervalBPV.description: Number of BPVs (Bi-Polar Violations) , encountered by a DS3 interface in the specified 15 minute interval. This object is relevant only for Electrical Line of Fomi-E3/T3.

prtDs3IntervalLCE.name: prtDs3IntervalLCE
prtDs3IntervalLCE.description: Number of LCE (Link Code Errors) encountered by a DS3 interface in the specified 15 minute interval. This object is relevant only for Optical Links of Fomi-E3/T3.

prtDs3IntervalStatus.name: prtDs3IntervalStatus
prtDs3IntervalStatus.description: The statuses of the current interval: 0 - Valid. 1 - redundantLinkSwitch - the link has been switched by a redundancy mechanism. 2 - discontinuity - module was partialy out. 4 - notValid - module is out.

prtDs3TotalUAS.name: prtDs3TotalUAS
prtDs3TotalUAS.description: Number of UASs (Unavailable Seconds) , encountered by a DS3 interface in the previous 96 intervals. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.

prtDs3TotalBPV.name: prtDs3TotalBPV
prtDs3TotalBPV.description: Number of BPVs (Bi-Polar Violations) , encountered by a DS3 interface in the previous 96 intervals. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.

prtDs3TotalLCE.name: prtDs3TotalLCE
prtDs3TotalLCE.description: Number of LCE (Link Code Errors) encountered by a DS3 interface in the previous 96 intervals. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.

prtDs3TotalSES.name: prtDs3TotalSES
prtDs3TotalSES.description: Number of SES (Severely Errored Seconds) encountered by a DS3 interface in the previous 96 intervals. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.

radSysWanEvents.name: radSysWanEvents
radSysWanEvents.description: The events for RAD Wan products.

radRBHEEvents.name: radRBHEEvents
radRBHEEvents.description: The events for RAD Stackable products.

radRBHTEvents.name: radRBHTEvents
radRBHTEvents.description: The events for RAD Stackable products.

radSysPSEvents.name: radSysPSEvents
radSysPSEvents.description: The events for RAD Packet Switch (PS) products.

radSysRtrEvents.name: radSysRtrEvents
radSysRtrEvents.description: The events for RAD Router products.

radSysAtmEvents.name: radSysAtmEvents
radSysAtmEvents.description: The events for RAD ATM products.

agnHwVersion.name: agnHwVersion
agnHwVersion.description: ASCII string for description and display of the agent hardware version, as it is known by the agent software.The user can update the version upon request when he changes components in the agent's module

agnTrapMask.name: agnTrapMask
agnTrapMask.description: The value of this attribute determines the type of traps the agent should mask and not send to the management console. The value is differently determined for different products. There are mainly two methods: - an integer number, specifying the traps' severity. - a sum of 2**n, where n is a bit assigned to a certain masked trap group. User should consult the product specification, to find out the method employed.

agnTrapValue.name: agnTrapValue
agnTrapValue.description: The value of the trap decoded in internal RAD format. Full description is given in the Trap definition file

agnChangeCnt.name: agnChangeCnt
agnChangeCnt.description: The number of changes in system configuration that were reported to the manager since last cold start

agnSpecific.name: agnSpecific
agnSpecific.description: Object identifier of entity containing additional information regarding this instance.

agnConfigMsg.name: agnConfigMsg
agnConfigMsg.description: Full configuration message coded in internal RAD application format. This entry describes agent's configuration. For MP-2200 R3, this object describes agent's support of the V5.1 feature: 1 octet ; bit 0 (LSB). '1' - V5.1 feature is supported '0' - V5.1 feature is not supported.

mngTrapIpTable.name: mngTrapIpTable
mngTrapIpTable.description: This table indicates the destination address of the traps. Internally it will be limited to ten addresses.

mngID.name: mngID
mngID.description: This value indicates an index of a specific IP address

mngIP.name: mngIP
mngIP.description: This value indicates the destination address of the traps. IP 0.0.0.0 removes the entry.

mngIPMask.name: mngIPMask
mngIPMask.description: This value indicates the mask of the destination addresses of the traps.

mngTrapMask.name: mngTrapMask
mngTrapMask.description: The value of this attribute determines the type of traps the agent should mask and not send to this NMS. The value is differently determined for different products. There are mainly two methods: - an integer number, specifying the traps' severity. - a sum of 2**n, where n is a bit assigned to a certain masked trap group. User should consult the product specification, to find out the method employed.

mngAlarmTrapMask.name: mngAlarmTrapMask
mngAlarmTrapMask.description: The value of this object determines the alarm traps that the agent should mask (not send to this manager). The value is an Octet String, where each bit is assigned to a certain trap. If the bit = 1, the trap will be masked. If the bit = 0, the trap will not be masked. For more details on the specific alarm traps masked, see product specification.

agnIndication.name: agnIndication
agnIndication.description: Attribute describing the state of the entity the agent is responsible for. In case of a modular entity, the value of this attribute will be according to the component which is in the worst state. The order of severity (from top to bottom) is: critical-> major (or faulty)-> minor-> event-> warning-> normal (off).

agnMonitorModeCmd.name: agnMonitorModeCmd
agnMonitorModeCmd.description: Setting this attribute to ON, will enforce the agent to change its mode of operation to Monitor Mode

agnLed.name: agnLed
agnLed.description: This entry specifies the LEDs status of the agent module . Each led will be represented by 4 bits where the first 2 bits (left) will specify the status : (00=NA, 01=OFF, 10=ON, 11=BLINK), and the next two bits (right) will specify the color : (00=GREEN, 01=RED, 10=YELLOW, 11=GRAY)

trapTable.name: trapTable
trapTable.description: This table includes the last few traps generated by the agent, for future retrieval. The table has a limited capacity. If traps are not retrieved in proper time, they will be over-written by new traps

trapID.name: trapID
trapID.description: This value indicates an index of a specific trap

trapVal.name: trapVal
trapVal.description: This value is the actual ASCII description of the trap.

trapTimeSinceOccurrence.name: trapTimeSinceOccurrence
trapTimeSinceOccurrence.description: This value indicates the amount of time passed since the occurrence of the event that trigger this trap.

fileServerIP.name: fileServerIP
fileServerIP.description: The IP address of the server from which the file is loaded

fileName.name: fileName
fileName.description: The name of the file to be loaded. For protection, read returns NULL.

fileTransCmd.name: fileTransCmd
fileTransCmd.description: The command to be executed on fileName at fileServerIP.

tftpStatus.name: tftpStatus
tftpStatus.description: Status of tftp session. When a session ended with success, the tftpStatus should be endedOk(6). Before restarting a tftp session, the NMS should set the tftpStatus to noOp(2). That's the reason of MAX-ACCESS read-write to this field.

tftpError.name: tftpError
tftpError.description: The MSB represents the standard error code. The LSB represents the private error code. 0x0000 is No Error 0x0100 is File Not Found 0x0400 is Illegal TFTP operation 0x0500 is Unknown transfer ID 0x0001 is Server Overflow 0x0002 is No empty UDP port 0x0003 is No empty connection 0x0004 is Illegal File Mode 0x0007 is Illegal PDU size

fileTransferToSubSystems.name: fileTransferToSubSystems
fileTransferToSubSystems.description: This object represents the sub-systems the fileTransCmd refers to. It should be used when a system is divided to sub-systems and each sub-system (or part of them) can have a different SW/Configuration. Each bit of this object will represent one of the sub-systems. Bit='1' - APPLY to respective sub-system Bit='0' - DO NOT APPLY to respective sub-system For the meaning of each bit, see product's specification. User will select the sub-systems envolved by filling-in the bits that represent these sub-systems. In this case, the file represented by 'fileName' will include several parts, each representing one of the sub-systems. The agent will refer only to the part/s indicated by this object. 0 Octet Strings = not applicable DEFVAL = 0h for the products that support this object.

fileNameWithinProduct.name: fileNameWithinProduct
fileNameWithinProduct.description: The file name used by the product within the product file system.

intSwdlTable.name: intSwdlTable
intSwdlTable.description: This parameters table is for internal Software down load. It also includes data about all files contained in the Object from which down-load is performed.

intSwdlObjIdx.name: intSwdlObjIdx
intSwdlObjIdx.description: The index of the object from which down-load is performed.

intSwdlFileIdx.name: intSwdlFileIdx
intSwdlFileIdx.description: The index of the files included in intSwdlObjIdx. One of these files can be selected to be internally downloaded.

intSwdlFileSwVer.name: intSwdlFileSwVer
intSwdlFileSwVer.description: The software version of the file.

intSwdlSwDate.name: intSwdlSwDate
intSwdlSwDate.description: The software version date of the file.

intSwdlCmd.name: intSwdlCmd
intSwdlCmd.description: The command to down-load a SW file to an object. The Agent will change the value of this MIB object to off(2) automatically, after accepting the command.

intSwdlToSubSystem.name: intSwdlToSubSystem
intSwdlToSubSystem.description: This object defines the subsystem for download. Bit='1'- APPLY to respective sub system. Bit='0'- DO NOT APPLY to respective sub system. For more details see product specification. For every octet bit0=LSB, bit7=MSB

swdlStatusTable.name: swdlStatusTable
swdlStatusTable.description: This parameters table is for software download status. It also includes data about the files down-loaded or attempted to be down-loaded.

swdlStatusTypeIdx.name: swdlStatusTypeIdx
swdlStatusTypeIdx.description: The index of the down-load type (e.g. external (1) or internal (2)).

swdlStatusIdx.name: swdlStatusIdx
swdlStatusIdx.description: The index of the status rows.

swdlStatusSlot.name: swdlStatusSlot
swdlStatusSlot.description: The slot of the updated (or attempted to be updated) object.

swdlStatusSubSystem.name: swdlStatusSubSystem
swdlStatusSubSystem.description: The subsystem that updated (or attempted to be updated).

swdlStatusStatus.name: swdlStatusStatus
swdlStatusStatus.description: The status of the down load process. Value: Fail (2), OK (3), InProcess (4).

swdlStatusTime.name: swdlStatusTime
swdlStatusTime.description: This MIB parameter indicates the time SW download was finished. The format shuld be YYYY-MM-DD, hh:mm:ss

clearDwldStatusLog.name: clearDwldStatusLog
clearDwldStatusLog.description: This object clears the status log. Value: off(2), external(3), internal(4) The Agent will change the value of this MIB object to off(2) automatically, after accepting the command .

autoFileTransferTable.name: autoFileTransferTable
autoFileTransferTable.description: Scheduling configuration table for Agent initiated file transfer.

autoFileTransferType.name: autoFileTransferType
autoFileTransferType.description: This object defines the type of file to be transferred by agent.

autoFileTransferServerIp.name: autoFileTransferServerIp
autoFileTransferServerIp.description: This object defines the IP Address of the server to which the file is uploaded.

autoFileTransferFileName.name: autoFileTransferFileName
autoFileTransferFileName.description: This object defines the name of the file to be uploaded.

autoFileTransferScheduling.name: autoFileTransferScheduling
autoFileTransferScheduling.description: This object defines schedule for TFTP Automatic session(s) initiated by Agent, according to the value selected: now - initiate immediate single session. recurrence- initiate single session 'every M time units'. or 'every N occurrences' or upon both, (earliest event). Time reccurence period (M) is defined by fileTransferTimeRecurrence. Occurrence reccurence (N) is defined by fileTransferOccurrenceRecurrence. Zero value means that the object is not relevant (not taken into account for the recurrence). It is invalid that both will have zero values in our case (recurrence). When both are non zero, file is transferred upon earliest event

autoFileTransferTimeRecurrence.name: autoFileTransferTimeRecurrence
autoFileTransferTimeRecurrence.description: This object defines time reccurence interval, e.g. M can be 'every M days', 'every M hours' etc. Zero is used to indicate there's no time reccurence (0= notApplicable). This object is taken into account only if autoFileTransferScheduling = recurrence For LA-110 time units are days.

autoFileTransferOccurrenceRecurrence.name: autoFileTransferOccurrenceRecurrence
autoFileTransferOccurrenceRecurrence.description: This object defines Occurrence reccurence interval, e.g N can be in 'every N alarms', 'every N log entries' etc. zero is used to indicate There's no Event Reccurence. (0= notApplicable) This object is taken into account only if autoFileTransferScheduling = recurrence Occurence Type (Alarms, etc.) is according to autoFileTransferType.

systemReset.name: systemReset
systemReset.description: Reset action to be performed on the system.

physicalConnectorTable.name: physicalConnectorTable
physicalConnectorTable.description: This table includes the connector type of ports or interfaces.

portIdx.name: portIdx
portIdx.description: This object is an index of the specific port or interface. For a port, the index will be as agreed between agent and application. For an interface, ifIndex may be used.

physicalConnector.name: physicalConnector
physicalConnector.description: The connector of the port/interface. other - none of the specified connectors none - no connector.

portOptWaveLength.name: portOptWaveLength
portOptWaveLength.description: Wave Length of an Optical interface/port in [nm] and specification if Laser or not. notApplicable - for non-optical ports.

portOptMode.name: portOptMode
portOptMode.description: Laser Mode of an Optical Laser interface/port. notApplicable - for non-Laser ports.

portBalance.name: portBalance
portBalance.description: This object is according to the port Impedance. For T1 - always balanced. For E1 - there are different impedance values for balanced and unbalanced.

prtSupervisoryIndex.name: prtSupervisoryIndex
prtSupervisoryIndex.description: The SP port index. For some products, having modules (cards): The LS byte of the integer is the port index 1..255. The MS byte is different than 0 only if the port belongs to a module. In that case it is the module number. For other products' index see their specification.

prtSupervisoryRate.name: prtSupervisoryRate
prtSupervisoryRate.description: This attribute indicates the operation rate (speed) of the port. auto - automatic rate selection, by the agent.

prtSupervisoryDataBits.name: prtSupervisoryDataBits
prtSupervisoryDataBits.description: This attribute indicates the number of data bits in an async frame

prtSupervisoryParity.name: prtSupervisoryParity
prtSupervisoryParity.description: This attribute indicates the parity mode in an async frame

prtSupervisoryStopBits.name: prtSupervisoryStopBits
prtSupervisoryStopBits.description: This attribute indicates the parity mode in an async frame.

prtSupervisoryUsage.name: prtSupervisoryUsage
prtSupervisoryUsage.description: This attribute indicates the usage of the SP port.

prtSupervisoryInterface.name: prtSupervisoryInterface
prtSupervisoryInterface.description: This attribute indicates the supervisory port interface.

prtSupervisoryRoutProtocol.name: prtSupervisoryRoutProtocol
prtSupervisoryRoutProtocol.description: This attribute indicates the routing protocol of the port. notApplicable - for DP.

prtPerfTable.name: prtPerfTable
prtPerfTable.description: This table includes G.826 ports or interfaces.

prtPerfIdx.name: prtPerfIdx
prtPerfIdx.description: This object is an index of the specific port or interface. For a port, the index will be as agreed between agent and application. For an interface, ifIndex may be used.

prtPerfPeriodRef.name: prtPerfPeriodRef
prtPerfPeriodRef.description: This object is an index that specifies which period of time, the next 5 objects refer to. currentPeriod - the period since last prtPerfSaveAndResetCmd received or since Start-up (if no prtPerfSaveAndResetCmd was received since Start-up) until now. lastPeriod - the period between last two commands of prtPerfSaveAndResetCmd. - If only one command occured since Start-up: the period between Start-up and last command. - If no command occured since Start-up: this period will not actually exist. In this case, he following 5 objects will be 0.

prtPerfElapsedTime.name: prtPerfElapsedTime
prtPerfElapsedTime.description: Elapsed Time in seconds. - for prtPerfPeriodRef=currentPeriod: The period since last prtPerfSaveAndResetCmd received or since Start-up (if no prtPerfSaveAndResetCmd was received since Start-up) until now. - for prtPerfPeriodRef=lastPeriod: The value of prtPerfElapsedTime when last prtPerfSaveAndResetCmd was received.

prtPerfUAS.name: prtPerfUAS
prtPerfUAS.description: Number of Unavailable Seconds for the reference period (prtPerfPeriodRef).

prtPerfES.name: prtPerfES
prtPerfES.description: Number of Errored Seconds for the reference period (prtPerfPeriodRef).

prtPerfSES.name: prtPerfSES
prtPerfSES.description: Number of Severely Errored Seconds for the reference period (prtPerfPeriodRef).

prtPerfBBE.name: prtPerfBBE
prtPerfBBE.description: Number of Background Block (or Frame) Errors for the reference period (prtPerfPeriodRef).

prtPerfBlocksPerSec.name: prtPerfBlocksPerSec
prtPerfBlocksPerSec.description: Blocks per second (or frames per second) of the port/interface indicated by portIdx. This object is constant for a certain port/interface. It is not affected by the prtPerfPeriodRef index.

prtPerfTimeTag.name: prtPerfTimeTag
prtPerfTimeTag.description: Time Tag of Last Period: sysUpTime when last prtPerfSaveAndResetCmd was executed. This object is applicable only for prtPerfPeriodRef=lastPeriod. For prtPerfPeriodRef=currentPeriod, the value will always be 0.

prtPerfSaveAndResetCmd.name: prtPerfSaveAndResetCmd
prtPerfSaveAndResetCmd.description: A command per port/interface, to Save data of Current Period in Last Period data-set and start a new counting period for Current Period. This object is applicable only for prtPerfPeriodRef=currentPeriod. Setting this object to on(3) for prtPerfPeriodRef=last, will cause the agent to return: Bad Value response. When setting validly this object to on(3), agent will perform the required command and will reset automatically the value of this object to off(2). Setting this object to off(2), will do nothing.

prtTestTable.name: prtTestTable
prtTestTable.description: This table includes test data for ports or interfaces.

prtTestIdx.name: prtTestIdx
prtTestIdx.description: This object is an index of the specific port or interface. For a port, the index will be as agreed between agent and application. For an interface, ifIndex may be used.

prtTestCmdAndStatus.name: prtTestCmdAndStatus
prtTestCmdAndStatus.description: Setting this object to a value as detailed further on (except 0) will initiate a test on the specific port. The test/s requested will be set according to the respective bit. The value of this object will be a sum of (2**n), where n is the Bit: TEST BIT VALUE ----------- --- ------ reserved 0 1 PayloadLoop=RLB 1 (=Remote Loopback) 2 LineLoop=DIG 2 (=Digital) 4 OtherLoop 3 8 InwardLoop=LLB 4 (=Local Loopback) 16 BERT 5 32 LC 6 64 ToneInjection 7 128 Inband 8 256 BERT Remote 9 512 Downstream-AIS 10 1024 Upstream-AIS 11 2048 Rem-Loop-on-Rem-Unit 12 4096 e.g : If the requested value is 20 -> 010100 -> Bits 2 & 4 are set -> the requested tests are : LineLoopback=DIG InwardLoopback=LLB Not all tests combinations are valid. For valid test combination, see each product's specification. For LRS52, only single test is allowed simultaneously The terminology and order of the first tests (except BERT) is according to the one used for Test Status of DS1 and DS3 standards. The notations : RLB, LLB, DIG are the most used in RAD's products, but they can be different. For exact definition see product's spec. Setting this object to stop (value=0 ; all bits are 0), will stop all the user requested tests running on the selected port. When no test is running on the port, the Get value (test status) will be 0. PayloadLoop=RLB The received signal at this interface is looped through the device. Typically the received signal is looped back for retransmission after it has passed through the device's framing function. LineLoop=DIG The received signal at this interface does not go through the device (minimum penetration) but is looped back out. OtherLoop Loopbacks that are not defined here. InwardLoop=LLB The sent signal at this interface is looped back through the device. LC This loop is applicable only for HSSI interface, towards the router . ToneInjection This loop is applicable for analog voice (like FXS). Downstream-AIS E1 AIS signal (all ones) is transmitted in the relevant channel toward the STM-1 line. Upstream-AIS E1 AIS signal (all ones) is generated in the relevant channel toward the local received tributary channel output. Rem-Loop-on-Rem-Unit Request from far end device to activate remote loopback towards near-end device.

prtBertCounter.name: prtBertCounter
prtBertCounter.description: This object indicates the number of BERT errors encountered during the BERT operation. It is valid only when BERT (Bit Error Rate Test) is active on the specific port. The Counter starts from zero (0) anytime BERT is initiated.

prtTestInitiator.name: prtTestInitiator
prtTestInitiator.description: This object indicates who initiated this port's test/s.

prtTestTimeout.name: prtTestTimeout
prtTestTimeout.description: This object is applicable only when a single test is running. It indicates the test activation timeout in minutes. When the timeout expires, the test is stopped. Value of 0 indicates test may run Forever

prtParamTable.name: prtParamTable
prtParamTable.description: This table includes general port parameters. The meaning is different for every product that supports it due to a general parameter - prtControlCnfg. For ACE2002: -This table is used as a mechanism to create the next interface index. The algorithm description: The NMS will send the agent the following get command: get(nextIfIndex.index), where index=interface on which the new index is dependent on. Upon this command the agent will generate and return the new index to the NMS. - This table is partially supported according to the interface type. Upon getNext function the irrelevant parameters will be skipped.

prtParamIdx.name: prtParamIdx
prtParamIdx.description: This object is an index of the specific port or interface. For a port, the index will be as agreed between agent and application. For an interface, ifIndex may be used. For ACE2002: This parameter is the physical layer ifIndex of the slot on which the NMS requires the next interface index.

prtControlCnfg.name: prtControlCnfg
prtControlCnfg.description: This object may be used for port RW general parameter/s. For detailed meaning, see product's spec. Supported by: PRBi-E3/T3. For ACE2002: This parameter will include the value of the new index generated by agent. For Optimux-T3 and OP-155-1: This parameter will be used for Release Remote LLB Command: on=2= Set value only. Command to release LLB of Remote Unit. Agent will return automatically to 'off' value after performing the command. off=3=Get value only. For LA140 This parameter will be used as EchoCanceler per timeslot notApplicable = 1 Echo canceler is not applicable. off = 2 Echo Canceler is disabled on = 3 Echo Canceler is enabled For FCD-155 This parameter will be used to select the port that is clock source for a PDH port, For E1/T1 PDH VC12/VT1.5 = 2 SDH/SONET = 3 For E3/T3 PDH VC3/DS3 = 2 SDH/SONET = 3 For ACE-52 This parameter will be used as Transmit Frame Type, i.e. which type of frame the corresponding bridge port will transmit: Untagged = 2 Tagged = 3 .

prtParamClkSrc.name: prtParamClkSrc
prtParamClkSrc.description: The source of Transmit Clock. 'loopTiming' or 'loopback' indicates that the recovered receive clock is used as the transmit clock. 'localTiming' or 'internal' indicates that a local clock source is used or when an external clock is attached to the box containing the interface. 'throughTiming' or 'external' indicates that recovered receive clock from another card or interface is used as the transmit clock. 'adaptive' indicates that the clock is recovered according to the received data flow rate. 'master' and 'fallback' values may be used RO to indicate active clock.

prtParamResetStatsCmd.name: prtParamResetStatsCmd
prtParamResetStatsCmd.description: Reset statistics of the selected port.

prtParamLastResetStatsTime.name: prtParamLastResetStatsTime
prtParamLastResetStatsTime.description: The value of MIB II's sysUpTime object at the last time that prtParamResetStatsCmd was Set to on(3) for this port. If prtParamResetStatsCmd was never Set to on(3) since last re-initialization of the agent, then this object contains a zero value. This object enables calculating the running time of Statistics counters for this port, by: [sysUpTime-prtParamLastResetStatsTime]. For some devices other types of 'Reset' may affect this parameter

prtParamClearAlarm.name: prtParamClearAlarm
prtParamClearAlarm.description: Setting this attribute to ON, will enforce a clear operation on the Port Alarms. Upon completion, the value will automatically change to off(2).

prtParamLeds.name: prtParamLeds
prtParamLeds.description: This entry specifies the LEDs status of the port. Each led is represented by 4 bits where the first 2 bits (left) specify the status : (00=NA, 01=OFF, 10=ON, 11=BLINK), and the next two bits (right) specify the color : (00=GREEN, 01=RED, 10=YELLOW, 11=GRAY). The order of the LEDS is from top to bottom, left to right: For each row starting from the top, the LEDS are returned from left to right.

prtIpParamTable.name: prtIpParamTable
prtIpParamTable.description: A table - Parameters for IP Ports.

prtIpParamConfigIdx.name: prtIpParamConfigIdx
prtIpParamConfigIdx.description: This object indicates the Configuration number (1..255) referred. Value of 255 specifies the TmpCnfg (Scratch). For products having Agent and Edit configurations, Write operation for the table entries is allowed only to Config=255.

prtIpParamSlotIdx.name: prtIpParamSlotIdx
prtIpParamSlotIdx.description: This object indicates a unique number of the slot position in which the module is inserted. notApplicable = 255 (for products that don't have slots). For KM: kmxMlA (103), kmxMlB (104).

prtIpParamIdx.name: prtIpParamIdx
prtIpParamIdx.description: This object indicates a unique Port Index.

prtIpParamMediaMode.name: prtIpParamMediaMode
prtIpParamMediaMode.description: This object indicates the real Media Mode.

prtIpParamMediaRate.name: prtIpParamMediaRate
prtIpParamMediaRate.description: This object indicates the real Media Rate (Mbps).

prtIpParamMngVlanSupport.name: prtIpParamMngVlanSupport
prtIpParamMngVlanSupport.description: Management VLAN support (Tagging). no - No support of VLAN Tagging. yes - 4 VLAN bytes will be added to the frame.

prtIpParamRingMode.name: prtIpParamRingMode
prtIpParamRingMode.description: This object indicates If Ring Mode is enabled or not.

prtIpParamProtIpEnable.name: prtIpParamProtIpEnable
prtIpParamProtIpEnable.description: This object indicates whether a list of Protected IP Addresses is enabled or not. This object is applicable only if prtIpParamRingMode=enable.

prtIpParamTrafficPriority.name: prtIpParamTrafficPriority
prtIpParamTrafficPriority.description: This object indicates the traffic priority of this port.

prtIpParamRemoteIP.name: prtIpParamRemoteIP
prtIpParamRemoteIP.description: This is the IP Address of the remote device that is connected to the current device (Point to Point Application). It is used for sending OAM packets on the LAN to the remote side in order to check that the connection is OK.

prtIpParamMaxTxBandwidth.name: prtIpParamMaxTxBandwidth
prtIpParamMaxTxBandwidth.description: This object shows the Max Bandwidth allowed on the LAN. Full - means that a Maximum of 100 Mega Byte Rate may go through the LAN. e1(3) means that the maximum is an E1 rate. t1(4) is for a maximum of a T1 rate.

prtIpParamTos.name: prtIpParamTos
prtIpParamTos.description: TOS = Type of Service transmitted. Valid values: 0..255.

prtIpParamVlanSupport.name: prtIpParamVlanSupport
prtIpParamVlanSupport.description: VLAN support (Tagging). 'no' - No support of VLAN Tagging. 'yes' - 4 VLAN bytes will be added to the frame.

prtIpParamDoubleTagVlanId.name: prtIpParamDoubleTagVlanId
prtIpParamDoubleTagVlanId.description: VLAN Identifier of the Double Tagging VLAN.

prtIpParamDoubleTagVlanPriority.name: prtIpParamDoubleTagVlanPriority
prtIpParamDoubleTagVlanPriority.description: VLAN Frame priority of the Double Tagging VLAN.

prtIpParamVlanTagging.name: prtIpParamVlanTagging
prtIpParamVlanTagging.description: VLAN Tagging. 'unmodified' - No change will be done to the Frame. 'tag' - Add Tag to Untagged Frames. 'doubleTag' - Add Tag to all Frames. 'doubleTagAndFallBack' - Double Tagging will have different rules for VLANs that this port is member in, than these it is not a member in. 'untag' - Remove Tag from tagged frames.

prtIpParamRateLimit.name: prtIpParamRateLimit
prtIpParamRateLimit.description: The maximum rate permitted to transfer via this port, in Kbps.

prtIpParamDefInterface.name: prtIpParamDefInterface
prtIpParamDefInterface.description: The Default Interface for packets with unresolved destination subnet. For internal-X port: 100 + X .

prtIpParamMng.name: prtIpParamMng
prtIpParamMng.description: This object indicates whether Management is enabled/disabled via this port.

prtClkSrcTable.name: prtClkSrcTable
prtClkSrcTable.description: A table - Parameters for master and fallback clock source of ports .

prtClkSrcCnfgIdx.name: prtClkSrcCnfgIdx
prtClkSrcCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg(1..255) being accessed ; Idx of 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

prtClkSrcPrtIdx.name: prtClkSrcPrtIdx
prtClkSrcPrtIdx.description: This object indicates a unique Port Index (receiving clock). Refer to device specification for port Index

prtClkSrcIdx.name: prtClkSrcIdx
prtClkSrcIdx.description: An index in the table. master - refers Master clock parameters fallback - refers Fallback clock parameters

prtClkSrcMode.name: prtClkSrcMode
prtClkSrcMode.description: This entry indicates the source the nodal timing is locked to.

prtClkSrcPrt.name: prtClkSrcPrt
prtClkSrcPrt.description: This entry is valid only when working in rxClk mode. It specifies the port from which the clock willl be taken. Refer to device specification for source port Index

systemResetAllStatsCmd.name: systemResetAllStatsCmd
systemResetAllStatsCmd.description: Reset statistics of all ports and connections of the device.

systemClearTablesCmd.name: systemClearTablesCmd
systemClearTablesCmd.description: tempCnfgTables - Set *RowStatus = destroy for all entries of some tables having *RowStatus object, for temporary configuration only! (255). For the relevant tables, see product's specification. This object should be used by WAN product applications before performing the Update operation, in order to clear old entries of these tables. For MP-104/204 the entries will be destroyed for cnfg=1. off - agent will automatically change to this value, after performing the command.

systemParameter.name: systemParameter
systemParameter.description: This parameter can be used for different purposes: - TELNET session time-out in seconds. - Ace20: when trying to create row in a table that already has row with the same values, if set of values has to be unique in table, this attribute is set to the index of the existing row. - Optimux-T3: when CH interfaces are RJ-45, user can select via this object, the interface type for each Group of channels: T1 or E1: The selection will be a sum of the following Bits. '0' = T1 '1' = E1 Bit Group Value for each Bit having '1' 1 1 (CH-1..CH-8) 1 2 2 (CH-9..CH-12) 2 3 3 (CH-13..CH-20) 4 4 4 (CH-21..CH-28) 8 Examples: 15 = all Groups are selected to be E1 6 = Group 2 and Group 3 are selected to be E1 (Group 1 and Group 4 are T1). - FCD-A, FCD-M: user can select via this object the configuration used for Get values of MSDSL parameters that don't have configuration index. 1 =active configuration 255=temporary configuration. Set of this object should be done before Getting the MSDSL RW parameters. - Ace2002: This parameter indicates the number of intervals that were successfully uploaded upon statistics collection session. - FCD-IP, WR, FCD-IPD, LA-240: This parameter indicates whether Telnet Access is enabled/disabled: Values: 2 - Telnet Access is Disabled. 3 - Telnet Access is Enabled. -Vmux-110: This parameter value equals to maximum number of bundles. -Optimux-155: Simmilar usage to Optimux T3. user can select via this object, interface type T1 or E1 for each Group of channels (LIU): LIU group consists of 7 channels. Up to 12 LIUs are represented (84 T1 Channels). The selection will be a sum of the 2**n For each bit:'0' = T1 ,'1' = E1 Bit Group 1 1 (CH-1 .. CH-7) 2 2 (CH-8 .. CH-14) 3 3 (CH-15 ..CH-21) ... 9 9 (CH-56.. CH-63) ... 10 10 (CH-64..CH-70) 11 11 (CH-71..CH-77) 12 12 (CH-78..CH-84)

agnGlobalAlarmMask.name: agnGlobalAlarmMask
agnGlobalAlarmMask.description: The value of this attribute determines the alarm traps the agent should mask and not send to the managers. Each bit from a certain octet represents a certain alarm.

alarmSeverity.name: alarmSeverity
alarmSeverity.description: This object specifies the severity of the alarms.

agnTestStatus.name: agnTestStatus
agnTestStatus.description: Indicates the current test status (for all levels: system, card, port). This attribute will be set to: on(3): when there is at least one test in progress on the system/card/port off(2): when there is NO test in progress on the system/card/port

systemSaveAndResetAllStatsCmd.name: systemSaveAndResetAllStatsCmd
systemSaveAndResetAllStatsCmd.description: on - a command to Save data of Current Period in Last Period data-set and start a new counting period for Current Period. off - agent will automatically change to this value, after performing the command.

systemPsTable.name: systemPsTable
systemPsTable.description: This table describes the PS types of a device. Usage of this table is specified in the device's NMS SRS

systemPsIndex1.name: systemPsIndex1
systemPsIndex1.description: First Index. In HUBs: 1 = PS-A slot 2 = PS-B slot 3 = PS-C slot. In SA units: 1 = PS1 2 = PS2 Default = 1

systemPsIndex2.name: systemPsIndex2
systemPsIndex2.description: Second Index. In HUBs: 1 always. In SA units: 1 = Local 2 = Remote Default = 1.

systemPsType.name: systemPsType
systemPsType.description: The type of PS, for a stand-alone product. acDc - AC with rj45 DC. acPF - Power Feeding (phantom) box that is feeding another box by external AC. dcPF - Power Feeding (phantom) box that is feeding another box by external DC.

systemPsStatus.name: systemPsStatus
systemPsStatus.description: The Status of the PS unit.

systemPsHotSwap.name: systemPsHotSwap
systemPsHotSwap.description: Is PS unit hot swap or fixed.

agnFans.name: agnFans
agnFans.description: This entry specifies the FANs existence and status. Each fan will be represented by 2 bits, where the first bit (right) will specify the existence: (0= Not exist, 1=exist), and the left bit will specify it's status (0= OK, 1=FAIL), so for each fan: 00 - FAN does not exist 01 - FAN exists and OK (Low Mode) 10 - High Mode (FAN OK) 11 - FAN exists and is Failed bits 0-1 are for first fan bits 2-3 are for 2nd fan (if exists) bits 4-5 are for 3nd fan (if exists) bits 6-7 are for 4nd fan (if exists) bits 8-9 are for 5nd fan (if exists) bits 10-11 are for 6nd fan (if exists) bits 12-13 are for 7nd fan (if exists) bits 14-15 are for 8nd fan (if exists).

agnSendTrapParameter.name: agnSendTrapParameter
agnSendTrapParameter.description: This object specifies if the agent will attach a specific parameter to a trap. For ACE2002 the agent will attach or not the openViewSeverity parameter according to the value of this parameter: 1 - will attach openViewSeverity. 0 - will not attach openViewSeverity.

agnSensorsStatus.name: agnSensorsStatus
agnSensorsStatus.description: This entry specifies the Sensors (Temperature sensors or others) existence and status. Each sensor will be represented by 2 bits, where the first bit (right) will specify the existence: (0= Not exist, 1=exist), and the left bit will specify it's status (0= OK, 1=FAIL), so for each sensor: 00 - sensor does not exist 01 - sensor exists and status is OK 11 - sensor exists and status is not OK ( e.g. temperature exceeds pre-defined threshold) bits 0-1 are for first sensor bits 2-3 are for 2nd sensor (if exists) and so on... Bit 0 is the LSB.

agnStationClockCard.name: agnStationClockCard
agnStationClockCard.description: This entry specifies the station clock card existence and status. notExist - station clock card (piggy) does not exist. notValid - station clock card exists but clock status is not valid. ok - station clock card exists, and its status is OK

xcIndexNext.name: xcIndexNext
xcIndexNext.description: This object contains an appropriate value to be used for xcIndex when creating entries in the xcTable. The value 0 indicates that no unassigned entries are available. To obtain the xcIndex value for a new entry, the manager issues a management protocol retrieval operation to obtain the current value of this object. After each retrieval, the agent should modify the value to the next unassigned index. After a manager retrieves a value the agent will determine through its local policy when this index value will be made available for reuse.

xcTable.name: xcTable
xcTable.description: Configuration of system cross-connect entries. The table follows the behavior described in RFC 2515, RFC 1604 regarding the creation deletion and modification of an entry within the table.

xcIfIndex1.name: xcIfIndex1
xcIfIndex1.description: The interface Index from the ifTable, which identify one side of the connection.

xcIfIndex2.name: xcIfIndex2
xcIfIndex2.description: The interface Index from the ifTable, which identifies the other side of the connection.

xcRowStatus.name: xcRowStatus
xcRowStatus.description: This parameter allows NMS to create/delete entries of this table.

xcDescr.name: xcDescr
xcDescr.description: A textual string containing information about the xc entry.

xcAdminStatus.name: xcAdminStatus
xcAdminStatus.description: The desired administrative status of this bi-directional cross-connect.

xcOperStatus.name: xcOperStatus
xcOperStatus.description: The operational status of this bi-directional cross-connect.

xcAttachedIfType.name: xcAttachedIfType
xcAttachedIfType.description: This object indicates if the specific VCC is already attached to any interface, and indicates the type of the interface. This object's purpose is to ease the checking to the NMS. notApplicable - used for entries that are not LAN (as HDLC), or when the VCC was attached to a bridge, or when this parameter is irrelevant. free - the LAN VCC wasn't attached yet to any router interface. routerAtm - attached to an ATM router interface. lis - attached to a LIS interface.

xcInputPriority.name: xcInputPriority
xcInputPriority.description: This object is the priority, by which the LAN frames will be internaly sent to the ATM HW. This parameter is applicable if atmNteMdlInputPriorityMechanism=enabled. 1 - Highest priority. Will be the first to be sent to the ATM HW. 4 - Lowest priority. Will be the last to be sent to the ATM HW.

xcBitMapping.name: xcBitMapping
xcBitMapping.description: This object maps this entry to a bit of an octet string. For ACE2002 this object maps the LAN VCC to the bit of the VLAN Port Lists. If the value is '0' then it means that this VCC is not mapped to a port list or it may be an HDSL entry.

modlParamTable.name: modlParamTable
modlParamTable.description: This table include parameters for system modules.

modlParamIndex.name: modlParamIndex
modlParamIndex.description: The module index. The index can be the slot number or any other module index as described in the specifications of the device. For Vmux-2100 device, the index will have values of: 1..4 for slots 1..4.

modlParamReset.name: modlParamReset
modlParamReset.description: Reset action to be performed on the module. Set the parameter will be done always to on(3) or factory (4). After performing the Reset operation, Agent will automatically set the parameter to off(2).

modlParamSwdlStatus.name: modlParamSwdlStatus
modlParamSwdlStatus.description: This parameter indicates whatever the swdl is in process or not.

modlParamLeds.name: modlParamLeds
modlParamLeds.description: This entry specifies the LEDs status of the module. Each led is represented by 4 bits where the first 2 bits (left) specify the status : (00=NA, 01=OFF, 10=ON, 11=BLINK), and the next two bits (right) specify the color : (00=GREEN, 01=RED, 10=YELLOW, 11=GRAY). The order of the LEDS is from top to bottom, left to right: For each row starting from the top, the LEDS are returned from left to right.

agnNearFarConnection.name: agnNearFarConnection
agnNearFarConnection.description: This parameter describes the connection between near-end and far-end agents.

agnTelnetAccess.name: agnTelnetAccess
agnTelnetAccess.description: Enable/Disable accessing the device via Telnet. disable - no one will be allowed to access the device via Telnet. enable - all users are allowed Telnet Access. managersOnly - Only manager stations listed in the manager's list are allowed.

agnWebAccess.name: agnWebAccess
agnWebAccess.description: Enable/Disable accessing the device via Web. disable - no one will be allowed to access the device via Web. enable - all users are allowed Web Access. managersOnly - Only manager stations listed in the manager's list are allowed.

ifCreateTable.name: ifCreateTable
ifCreateTable.description: The Interface Configuration Table. This table enables to create inferfaces of Entities.

ifCreateEntry.name: ifCreateEntry
ifCreateEntry.description: An entry in the Interface Configuration table.

ifCreateEntityType.name: ifCreateEntityType
ifCreateEntityType.description: This object indicates the Entity Type.

ifCreateEntityIdx.name: ifCreateEntityIdx
ifCreateEntityIdx.description: This object indicates the Entity Index.

ifCreateNumber.name: ifCreateNumber
ifCreateNumber.description: This object indicates the Interface Number.

ifCreateRowStatus.name: ifCreateRowStatus
ifCreateRowStatus.description: This object enables the user to create/delete entries in this table.

ifCreateType.name: ifCreateType
ifCreateType.description: This object indicates the Interface Type.

ifCreateIndex.name: ifCreateIndex
ifCreateIndex.description: This object indicates the ifIndex of the created Interface.

ifCreateConnectedTo.name: ifCreateConnectedTo
ifCreateConnectedTo.description: This object indicates the entity connected to the created Interface.

systemOamEntry.name: systemOamEntry
systemOamEntry.description: An entry in the OAM table.

systemOamCnfgIdx.name: systemOamCnfgIdx
systemOamCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg(1..255) being accessed ; Idx of 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

systemOamFrequency.name: systemOamFrequency
systemOamFrequency.description: Time in sec. between 2 OAM packets.

systemOamTimeoutCycles.name: systemOamTimeoutCycles
systemOamTimeoutCycles.description: No. of cycles the agent will send OAM packets without receiving a response from the remote device before declaring that the connection to the remote side is down - Time Out.

agnDeviceView.name: agnDeviceView
agnDeviceView.description: The view of the device (old look or new look).

bitMappingTable.name: bitMappingTable
bitMappingTable.description: This table maps bits of an octet string to an interface. For ACE-2002 this table is used to map bits of VLAN port lists to LAN VCC's. This table is the opposite view of the xcTable for xcBitMapping. It is used to ease the bit translation for the NMS.

bitMappingEntry.name: bitMappingEntry
bitMappingEntry.description: Each entry in the table describes a correlation of a bit location to an interface. For ACE-2002 - Upon creation of a new LAN VCC the agent will add an entry to this table that will define the bit location for that VCC.

bitMappingLocation.name: bitMappingLocation
bitMappingLocation.description: The bit location in an octet string.

bitMappingIndex.name: bitMappingIndex
bitMappingIndex.description: The interface index or any other index that should be mapped.

bitMappingView.name: bitMappingView
bitMappingView.description: A view of the bitMappingTable in one object - each entry in the biMappingTable will have the corresponding Bit of this object (bitMappingLocation) = '1'. For ACE-2002 it is used to describe all the existing LAN VCC's So that the NMS can easily calculate which VCC's can be selected as members for a VLAN, instead of reading all the bitMapping Table.

hostEntry.name: hostEntry
hostEntry.description: An entry in the Host Table. The hostParam1, hostParam2, and hostParam3 entries may have different use in different applications.

hostIndex.name: hostIndex
hostIndex.description: The Host Table Index. This index can have the same value as Host No.

hostDefaultNextHop.name: hostDefaultNextHop
hostDefaultNextHop.description: The host interface Default Next Hop address.

hostMode.name: hostMode
hostMode.description: This parameter represents the Host mode of operation. There can be different values for each application. For example: Not Applicable = 1.

hostParam1.name: hostParam1
hostParam1.description: This parameter represents the first Host parameter. There can be different values for each application. For example: Not Applicable = 1.

hostParam2.name: hostParam2
hostParam2.description: This parameter represents the 2nd Host parameter. There can be different values for each application.

hostParam3.name: hostParam3
hostParam3.description: This parameter represents the 3nd Host parameter. There can be different values for each application.

hostRowStatus.name: hostRowStatus
hostRowStatus.description: Creation/Deletion of rows in the table.

hostVlanTagging.name: hostVlanTagging
hostVlanTagging.description: Host VLAN support (Tagging). untag - No support of VLAN Tagging. tag - 4 VLAN bytes will be added to the frame.

agnDeviceCapabilities.name: agnDeviceCapabilities
agnDeviceCapabilities.description: Indicates the optional capabilities that are implemented by this device and are manageable through this MIB. For each capability 1 BIT is allocated in each Octet starting from the LSB. If the value of the BIT = 1, the capability is Enabled. If the value of the BIT = 0, the capability is Disabled. For bit assignment, refer to device specification. Capabilities example: Router - BIT 0 (0000 0001 = 01 Hex = 1 Decimal)

agnStoreCmd.name: agnStoreCmd
agnStoreCmd.description: Store command. inFlash (3) = store the current Agent configuration in Flash memory. Agent will perform the required command and change automatically the value of this object to off(2).

agnFunctionTable.name: agnFunctionTable
agnFunctionTable.description: This table is used in order to activate/deactivate device functions. The index indicates the function. Each function can be Enabled or Disabled.

agnFunction.name: agnFunction
agnFunction.description: This MIB object indicates the function that will be enabled or disabled in the device.

agnFunctionActivation.name: agnFunctionActivation
agnFunctionActivation.description: This MIB object indicates the activation of the current function.

agnManagerConfigPorts.name: agnManagerConfigPorts
agnManagerConfigPorts.description: This variable defines from which port/s this manager can manage the device. The value is a sum of 2**n, where n is a bit assigned to a certain port. For RIC-E1 and ETX 102 the value will be according to the ports combination: Network = bit 0 User= bit 1 For Example: All = 3.

agnEgressRateRange.name: agnEgressRateRange
agnEgressRateRange.description: This variable defines the valid ranges of egress rate. For example, for ETX 102: range 1 (2)= 128KBPS - 8MBPS, range 2 (3)= 256KBPS - 16MBPS, range 3 (4)= 512KBPS - 32MBPS, range 4 (5)= 1MBPS - 64MBPS, range 5 (6)= 1.5MBPS - 80MBPS.

ifPerfTable.name: ifPerfTable
ifPerfTable.description: Interface Performance Table. The propose of this table is to support statistics counters having 64 bit by using 2 parameters with syntax= Integer32. This is because SNMPv1 does not support Counter64 properly.

ifPerfEntry.name: ifPerfEntry
ifPerfEntry.description: An entry in the Interface Performance Table.

ifPerfCounterType.name: ifPerfCounterType
ifPerfCounterType.description: 2nd index of the ifPerfTable. This parameter represents the Counter Type. Each application can have a different association between this object's value and counter type - see relevant application spec. For VPLS-MTU application use the following values: 1= Rx Octets, 2= Tx Octets, 3= Rx Frames, 4= Tx Frames, 5= Rx Dropped Frames

ifPerfLowCounterPart.name: ifPerfLowCounterPart
ifPerfLowCounterPart.description: In order to support Counters having 64 bit length, the performance counter is divided into two 32 bit parameters as follows: [ 64 bit parameter ] = [ High 32 bit parameter ][ Low 32 bit parameter ]. This parameter holds the Low 32 bits of the counter, while the following parameter holds the High 32 bits of the counter.

ifPerfHighCounterPart.name: ifPerfHighCounterPart
ifPerfHighCounterPart.description: This parameter holds the High 32 bits of the counter (see description in the above parameter).

tftpStatusChangeTrap.name: tftpStatusChangeTrap
tftpStatusChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent whenever the status of tftp changed.

agnStatusChangeTrap.name: agnStatusChangeTrap
agnStatusChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent whenever the state of the entity the agent is responsible for changed. TDM devices will send agnTestStatus variable to indicate the current test status.

prtStatusChangeTrap.name: prtStatusChangeTrap
prtStatusChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent whenever the state of a port changed. Attached, will be parameter/s that indicate the new port status. The attached variables will be specified in the specifications of the products supporting this trap.

swdlStatusResult.name: swdlStatusResult
swdlStatusResult.description: This notification is sent when Software Down Load is finished. The attached object indicates the File Name.

intSwdlSlotFileMismatch.name: intSwdlSlotFileMismatch
intSwdlSlotFileMismatch.description: This notification is sent when the card in the chosen slot doesn't match the chosen file. The attached object indicates the File Name.

agnCounterChange.name: agnCounterChange
agnCounterChange.description: This notification is sent when the value of a specific Counter is changed. Agent can send as attached object the updated Counter. For details about this Counter and attached object, see spec of the relevant application.

prtClkSrcChangeTrap.name: prtClkSrcChangeTrap
prtClkSrcChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent upon any port clock change.

moduleFailTrap.name: moduleFailTrap
moduleFailTrap.description: This trap is sent upon a module failure.

moduleInitFailTrap.name: moduleInitFailTrap
moduleInitFailTrap.description: This trap is sent upon a module initialization failure.

clkSrcChangeTrap.name: clkSrcChangeTrap
clkSrcChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent upon any change in Clock Source.

agnUploadDataTrap.name: agnUploadDataTrap
agnUploadDataTrap.description: This trap is sent upon an upload data session termination. For more details see product specification.

enrollmentTrap.name: enrollmentTrap
enrollmentTrap.description: This trap is a periodically trap, which sent to manager untill Agent get any response (Get or Set) from this manager.

agnPowerFailureTrap.name: agnPowerFailureTrap
agnPowerFailureTrap.description: This trap is sent upon power failure. It is applicable for the following devices: 1. Devices having one PS unit, which sense the failure in advance, and still have time to send this trap before it goes off. 2. Devices having 2 PS units and send this trap in order to notify a failure in one of the units.

agnSystemParameterChangeTrap.name: agnSystemParameterChangeTrap
agnSystemParameterChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent upon any change of the systemParameter value.

agnConfigDBChecksumError.name: agnConfigDBChecksumError
agnConfigDBChecksumError.description: This trap indicates that the database currently stored in the non-volatile memory of the device is corrupted

agnAlarmBufferOverflow.name: agnAlarmBufferOverflow
agnAlarmBufferOverflow.description: This trap indicates that the quantity of alarm messages which have been written in the alarm buffer, since the last clear command, exceeds predefined threshold. (Buffer size) The new alarms are overwriting the oldest alarms (the first alarms written in the buffer). For LA-110,threshold value is 200 alarms.

agnAlarmBufferClear.name: agnAlarmBufferClear
agnAlarmBufferClear.description: This trap indicates that alarm buffer has been cleared.

agnParamtersValueChanged.name: agnParamtersValueChanged
agnParamtersValueChanged.description: This trap indicates that due to software upgrade, some of the parameters are assigned new values

agnDriverSwMismatch.name: agnDriverSwMismatch

dsx1CurrentCRCErrors.name: dsx1CurrentCRCErrors

dsx1IntervalLOS.description: The counter associated with the number of LOS seconds , encountered by a DS1 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

dsx1IntervalLOF.name: dsx1IntervalLOF
dsx1IntervalLOF.description: The counter associated with the number of OOF seconds, encountered by a DS1 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

dsx1IntervalLOC.name: dsx1IntervalLOC
dsx1IntervalLOC.description: Loss Of Cell delineation. Counts number of cells the ATM UNI cells receiver lost cells delineation .

dsx1IntervalAIS.name: dsx1IntervalAIS
dsx1IntervalAIS.description: The counter associated with the number of AIS seconds, encountered by a SONET interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

dsx1IntervalRAI.name: dsx1IntervalRAI
dsx1IntervalRAI.description: Remote Alarm Indication: Transmitted in the outgoing direction (toward the PABX) over FDL bits when the DS1 device detected an incoming Loss Of Frame. Received from the far end (PABX) over FDL when it detects a Loss of frame.

dsx1IntervalLOMF.name: dsx1IntervalLOMF
dsx1IntervalLOMF.description: Loss of Multi-Frame sequence in E1 time slot 16.

dsx1IntervalFEBE.name: dsx1IntervalFEBE
dsx1IntervalFEBE.description: Far End Block Errors, as reported in the first bit of frames 13 and 15, on multiframe E1 lines with CRC4, in one of the previous 96, individual, 15 minute intervals.

dsx1IntervalStatus.name: dsx1IntervalStatus
dsx1IntervalStatus.description: The statuses of the current interval: 0 - Valid. 1 - redundantLinkSwitch - the link has been switched by a redundancy mechanism. 2 - discontinuity - module was partialy out. 4 - notValid - module is out.

dsx1IntervalBPV.name: dsx1IntervalBPV
dsx1IntervalBPV.description: The counter associated with the number of BPV (Bi-Polar Violations) encountered by a DS1 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

dsx1IntervalLOCRCMF.name: dsx1IntervalLOCRCMF
dsx1IntervalLOCRCMF.description: Loss of CRC4 Multi-Frame sequence in E1.

dsx1IntervalLOFC.name: dsx1IntervalLOFC
dsx1IntervalLOFC.description: Counts the number of loss of frame events measured in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

dsx1XTotalTable.name: dsx1XTotalTable

dsx1XTotalEntry.description: An entry containing additional statistical counters applicable to a particular current table.

dsx1TotalBPV.name: dsx1TotalBPV
dsx1TotalBPV.description: The counter associated with the number of BPV (Bi-Polar Violations) encountered by a DS1 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.

dsx1TotalLOFC.name: dsx1TotalLOFC
dsx1TotalLOFC.description: The counter associated with the number loss of frames encountered by a DS1 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.

dsx1XConfigTable.name: dsx1XConfigTable
dsx1XConfigTable.description: An extension to the DS1 Configuration table.

dsx1XConfigEntry.name: dsx1XConfigEntry
dsx1XConfigEntry.description: An entry containing additional configuration parameters.

dsx1IdleCode.name: dsx1IdleCode
dsx1IdleCode.description: Byte pattern of the data received/transmitted in the E1T1 framer idle timeslots. Valid range: (0 - FF HEX).

dsx1LineMode.name: dsx1LineMode
dsx1LineMode.description: T1 device operation mode. Valid for T1 only.

dsx1dBTxGain.name: dsx1dBTxGain
dsx1dBTxGain.description: Transmit line Gain for T1 CSU line mode.

dsx1RxSensitivity.name: dsx1RxSensitivity
dsx1RxSensitivity.description: Determine the maximum attenuation of the receive signal that can be compensated for by the interface receive path. Not applicable for T1.

dsx1RestoreTime.name: dsx1RestoreTime
dsx1RestoreTime.description: Used to change the sync. algorithms to reduce the time required for the port to return to normal operation after a RED alarm.

dsx1TcFirstSignal.name: dsx1TcFirstSignal
dsx1TcFirstSignal.description: Trunk conditioning signal - value to be sent as a signal during the first 2.5 seconds after alarm detection. Range is 0x0..0xF. 0xFF is a NULL value. Valid for T1 only.

dsx1TcSignal.name: dsx1TcSignal
dsx1TcSignal.description: Trunk conditioning signal value after alarm detection. Range is 0x1..0xF for E1, and 0x0..0xF for T1.

dsx1TcPattern.name: dsx1TcPattern
dsx1TcPattern.description: Trunk conditioning data pattern to be sent upon a DS0 fail. Range is 0x0..0xFF.

dsx1Scramble.name: dsx1Scramble
dsx1Scramble.description: Scrambling is an operation that randomizes the bits of the payload of the ATM cell by a polynom. This operation helps with the error detection mechanism of the HEC. Not applicable for E1. active - will scramble/descramble the payload ATM cell notActive - will not scramble/descramble.

dsx1LineAdaptiveTimingMode.name: dsx1LineAdaptiveTimingMode
dsx1LineAdaptiveTimingMode.description: Enables end to end clock synchronization. Default value - off.

dsx1TxClockSource.name: dsx1TxClockSource
dsx1TxClockSource.description: The source of Transmit Clock. 'loopTiming' indicates that the recovered receive clock is used as the transmit clock. 'localTiming' indicates that a local clock source is used or when an external clock is attached to the box containing the interface. 'throughTiming' indicates that recovered receive clock from another interface is used as the transmit clock. 'adaptive' indicates that the clock is recovered according to the received data flow rate.

dsx1AisEnable.name: dsx1AisEnable
dsx1AisEnable.description: Enable/ disable AIS transmit when Ethernet cable (for TDMoIP) is out (disconnected).

dsx1TsEchoCancel.name: dsx1TsEchoCancel
dsx1TsEchoCancel.description: This parameter defines for each TS whether Echo-Cancellation is on. Each bit represents one TS as follow: First octet bit'0' = TS#1, bit'7' = TS#8, .. 2nd octet bit'0' = TS#9,.., 4th octet bit'7' = TS#32. Octets and bits order is from left to right: [31,30,..24] [23..16] [15..8] [7..0] MSB LSB MSB LSB MSB LSB MSB LSB For each bit values are: 0 - Echo-Cancellation off. 1 - Echo-Cancellation on.

dsx1EchoCancelerModule.name: dsx1EchoCancelerModule
dsx1EchoCancelerModule.description: This parameter indicates whether echo-cancellation module exists for this line.

dsx1PortFunction.name: dsx1PortFunction
dsx1PortFunction.description: This object determines the ATM Mode over the physical port. uni - The port will function as an ATM UNI. ces - The port will function as a CES. ima - The port will function as an IMA-ATM.

dsx1PortMultiplier.name: dsx1PortMultiplier
dsx1PortMultiplier.description: This object determines the data rate of each TS (Kbps units). This parameter is applicable for T1 only.

dsx1LeasedLine.name: dsx1LeasedLine
dsx1LeasedLine.description: This parameter defines whether Line mode is regular (non Leased Line mode) or transparent (Leased Line mode).

dsx1CsuLoop.name: dsx1CsuLoop
dsx1CsuLoop.description: This parameter defines whether CSU loop will be done locally (by IPmux) or will be transferred to the TDM device.

agnCnfgAlrFilterWindow.name: agnCnfgAlrFilterWindow
agnCnfgAlrFilterWindow.description: Window of time, in seconds. During this Window, the alarms filter is performed. Same Window for all agent alarms that need filtering. Upon end of the Window, the state of the alarm is updated and a new Window starts. If no alarm needs filtering, this object's value will not be used.

agnCnfgAlrTable.name: agnCnfgAlrTable
agnCnfgAlrTable.description: This table enables the user to set attributes to each alarm. Setting for a non-existing entry agnCnfgAlrMask, agnCnfgAlrInvert or agnCnfgAlrFilter to 'yes'(or yesAndSave for Mask) will add this new entry to the table. Setting for an existing entry agnCnfgAlrMask/ agnCnfgAlrInvert/agnCnfgAlrFilter (one or more) to 'no' (noAndSave for Mask) so that ALL these objects' values are 'no' , will delete this entry from the table. For agnCnfgAlrMask, only if [(last saved value=noAndSave) AND (new value is 'no' or 'noAndSave')] the object's value is considered 'no' for deleting the entry.

agnCnfgAlrCode.name: agnCnfgAlrCode
agnCnfgAlrCode.description: The alarm code. The following attributes refer this code.

agnCnfgAlrSlot.name: agnCnfgAlrSlot
agnCnfgAlrSlot.description: The alarm slot. The following attributes apply for the alarm code and slot selected. all = the attributes apply to all slots. notApplicable = the selected alarm is for system level.

agnCnfgAlrPort.name: agnCnfgAlrPort
agnCnfgAlrPort.description: The alarm port. The following attributes apply for the alarm code,slot and port selected. 200 = all = the attributes apply to all ports of the selected slot. When selected Slot is 'all', only 'all' or 'notApplicable' are valid Port selections. notApplicable = the selected alarm is for system or card level. =255 for MP =100 for DXC - For MP, valid cards' ports are: exPrt1(1)..exPrt16(16) inPrt1(101)..inPrt48 (148) - For DXC, the port index will include the Slot, as for all DXC tables: [(IO Slot+10)&n] ; n=odd for external ports n=even for internal ports.

agnCnfgAlrMask.name: agnCnfgAlrMask
agnCnfgAlrMask.description: An attribute defining the desired Mask state of an alarm . no - unmask (this command is not saved in agent's common database) noAndSave - unmask ; this command is saved in agent's common database yes - mask (this command is not saved in agent's common database) yesAndSave - mask ; this command is saved in agent's common database. Commands that are not saved, will be lost upon power-up or selected card removal.

agnCnfgAlrInvert.name: agnCnfgAlrInvert
agnCnfgAlrInvert.description: An attribute defining the desired Invert state of an alarm . no - not inverted. yes - inverted. For MP, it is not applicable for alarms that are currently OFF.

agnCnfgAlrFilter.name: agnCnfgAlrFilter
agnCnfgAlrFilter.description: An attribute defining if Filter is desired for the alarm . no - no filter. yes - filter activate. This filter is activated within a window of time defined by agnCnfgAlrFilterWindow. Its purpose is to avoid frequent changes of an alarm between ON/OFF states.

agnCnfgAlrFilterSet.name: agnCnfgAlrFilterSet
agnCnfgAlrFilterSet.description: This is a top threshold causing the alarm that passes it, to be declared Set (ON) at the end of the respective window of time. - For alarms defined by default as state alarms (minor,major) this value will be in [%]. - For alarms defined by default as events, this value will be an integer meaning how many times this event should appear at least, during the window in order to be considered ON. The maximum value will be 255. This value should be greater than the one of agnCnfgAlrFilterReset. Agents that do not support Alarms Filter, will return 0.

agnCnfgAlrFilterReset.name: agnCnfgAlrFilterReset
agnCnfgAlrFilterReset.description: This is a bottom threshold causing the alarm that does not pass it, to be declared Reset (ON) at the end of the respective window of time. - For alarms defined by default as state alarms (minor,major) this value will be in [%]. - For alarms defined by default as events, this value will be an integer meaning how many times this event should appear at most, during the window, in order to be considered OFF. This value should be less than the one of agnCnfgAlrFilterSet. Agents that do not support Alarms Filter, will return 0.

agnCnfgAlrSeverity.name: agnCnfgAlrSeverity
agnCnfgAlrSeverity.description: An attribute defining desired severity of an alarm code per slot/port

agnCnfgAlrReportTable.name: agnCnfgAlrReportTable
agnCnfgAlrReportTable.description: This table enables the user to configure the desired Alarm Reports according to alarms severity.

agnCnfgAlrReportType.name: agnCnfgAlrReportType
agnCnfgAlrReportType.description: The alarm report type. trap - traps will be sent only for alarms having the selected On/Off severity or higher. buffer - only alarms having the selected On/Off severity and higher, will be reported to the buffer. relay - relay contact will be activated only for alarms having the selected On severity or higher. For products having 2 relays, this is the R1 Relay. alrLedOn/alrLedBlink - user should select a higher severity (ReportOn) for alrLedBlink than for alrLedOn (Blinking Led means a more severe alarm than steady ON Led). alrLedOn - MTCL-1 Alarm Led will be ON only when agnSAlrStatusAll equals the selected severity or higher, but lower severity than that selected for 'alrLedBlink'. For products having 2 LEDs, this is the Minor LED. alrLedBlink - MTCL-1 Alarm Led will Blink only when agnSAlrStatusAll equals the selected severity or higher. For products having 2 LEDs, this is the Major LED. relay2 - relay 2 contact will be activated only for alarms having the selected On severity or higher. This is the R2 Relay.

agnCnfgAlrStartReportOn.name: agnCnfgAlrStartReportOn
agnCnfgAlrStartReportOn.description: This object specifies the severity from which alarms will be reported. Alarms having this severity or higher, will be reported. This object specifies the report severity only for alarms that turn to ON state. noReport - no Report at all (for any severity).

agnCnfgAlrStartReportOff.name: agnCnfgAlrStartReportOff
agnCnfgAlrStartReportOff.description: This object specifies the severity from which alarms will be reported. Alarms having this severity or higher, will be reported. This object specifies the report severity only for alarms that turn to OFF state. notApplicable - for 'relay','alrLedOn','alrLedBlink', 'relay2' report types, in MP. noReport - no Report at all (for any severity).
